1
00:00:00,040 --> 00:00:01,760
Haydar figured us out, bro.

2
00:00:01,880 --> 00:00:04,360
He came after me. He wanted info about you.

3
00:00:04,720 --> 00:00:07,040
I told him you had a brother who died.

4
00:00:09,560 --> 00:00:11,320
Whatever we do, it doesn’t work.

5
00:00:11,680 --> 00:00:14,640
Everything just brings them closer.
They’re practically glued together.

6
00:00:14,920 --> 00:00:18,880
We need to change direction
and focus on Mercan.

7
00:00:19,400 --> 00:00:21,560
In other words, she needs
to believe Ateş is bad.

8
00:00:22,000 --> 00:00:25,160
I’m warning the wife you play house with.

9
00:00:25,280 --> 00:00:29,160
Even if your marriage is fake,
her meeting with Nezir isn’t right.

10
00:00:29,360 --> 00:00:33,200
If something needs to be
said to my wife, I’ll say it.

11
00:00:33,480 --> 00:00:35,360
Don’t fight with your family because of me.

12
00:00:35,680 --> 00:00:37,680
They’ll always be in your life.

13
00:00:38,280 --> 00:00:39,440
But I won’t be here tomorrow.

14
00:00:39,760 --> 00:00:41,400
Ateş is in love with Mercan.

15
00:00:42,080 --> 00:00:45,440
What love, woman? Don’t drive me crazy!

16
00:00:45,720 --> 00:00:48,720
Love makes the impossible possible.

17
00:00:49,040 --> 00:00:50,600
Enough, Nermin! Stop it.

18
00:00:51,200 --> 00:00:53,840
As long as I’m here, no one dares.

19
00:00:54,080 --> 00:00:55,520
And don’t ever say that again.

20
00:00:55,880 --> 00:00:58,320
I don’t want you
exhausting yourself like this.

21
00:00:58,400 --> 00:00:59,840
Continue tomorrow.

22
00:01:01,120 --> 00:01:03,040
No need to worry about me.

23
00:01:04,080 --> 00:01:05,320
I promised the team I’d work.

24
00:01:05,920 --> 00:01:08,240
You made a promise to
us too in the beginning.

25
00:01:10,560 --> 00:01:12,040
What promise?

26
00:01:12,320 --> 00:01:15,000
What is she talking about? What promise?

27
00:02:30,320 --> 00:02:31,320
I

28
00:02:33,760 --> 00:02:34,800
Yes.

29
00:02:36,880 --> 00:02:38,280
What I wanted to say...

30
00:02:45,240 --> 00:02:47,040
Where is my olive pizza?

31
00:02:47,280 --> 00:02:50,320
I ordered an olive pizza, but
these aren't olive pizzas at all.

32
00:02:50,760 --> 00:02:52,560
Could they have been mixed up with yours?

33
00:02:53,600 --> 00:02:56,039
Sorry, I just walked in like
that, but my blood sugar dropped

34
00:02:56,040 --> 00:02:58,119
or something, and now my
hands and feet are shaking.

35
00:02:58,120 --> 00:03:00,519
I couldn't take it anymore, I
felt like I was going to faint

36
00:03:00,520 --> 00:03:02,680
maybe I did faint and
didn't even realise it.

37
00:03:03,240 --> 00:03:04,560
Since your hand is trembling

38
00:03:05,320 --> 00:03:07,760
you should have been content
with what you had in your hand

39
00:03:08,240 --> 00:03:10,160
I couldn't manage, Mr Ateş, I'm sorry

40
00:03:10,440 --> 00:03:11,640
I can't even see right now.

41
00:03:12,520 --> 00:03:13,600
Here it is!

42
00:03:14,080 --> 00:03:15,160
It's mixed up

43
00:03:16,640 --> 00:03:18,200
Alright, Yaşar, take your pizza

44
00:03:18,560 --> 00:03:19,600
and get lost!

45
00:03:22,240 --> 00:03:24,320
If you want a slice, I
can leave it, if you wish.

46
00:03:24,480 --> 00:03:25,560
Yaşar, get lost!

47
00:03:26,800 --> 00:03:27,840
Alright, Mr Ateş.

48
00:03:28,880 --> 00:03:30,920
I still can leave it, if you wish.

49
00:03:31,480 --> 00:03:33,280
Alright, Mr. Ateş.

50
00:03:38,800 --> 00:03:40,720
What you wanted to say?

51
00:03:48,160 --> 00:03:49,360
What I wanted to say...

52
00:03:59,280 --> 00:04:00,560
Enough already!

53
00:04:03,440 --> 00:04:04,680
What were you going to say?

54
00:04:05,200 --> 00:04:06,280
Never mind.

55
00:04:07,160 --> 00:04:08,920
It is not the right time or place, I guess.

56
00:04:10,360 --> 00:04:11,440
But...

57
00:04:17,080 --> 00:04:19,080
What just happened?

58
00:04:32,840 --> 00:04:34,000
Aww! That's a nice one.

59
00:04:37,280 --> 00:04:38,280
Nermin,

60
00:04:38,281 --> 00:04:40,119
Get rid of these already,
you've been staring

61
00:04:40,120 --> 00:04:42,040
at them since morning,
aren't you satisfied yet?

62
00:04:42,120 --> 00:04:43,160
You can stare more later.

63
00:04:44,760 --> 00:04:46,560
There are still ones I hadn't tried on yet.

64
00:04:47,000 --> 00:04:48,080
I'm checking them out

65
00:04:50,680 --> 00:04:53,720
Nermin, Where did you
get the money to buy them?

66
00:04:55,840 --> 00:04:58,280
Nermin I'm asking where
you got the money from?

67
00:04:58,400 --> 00:05:01,400
Yesterday, you were having an
attitude because I didn't give you money

68
00:05:02,080 --> 00:05:03,960
I took care of myself, Haydar.

69
00:05:06,080 --> 00:05:08,879
What do you mean, I took care of
myself? Don't mess up with me woman!

70
00:05:08,880 --> 00:05:10,480
Where did you get the money?

71
00:05:10,800 --> 00:05:12,440
I took Müzeyyen's necklace.

72
00:05:20,640 --> 00:05:21,680
Did you steal it?

73
00:05:24,200 --> 00:05:25,279
Of course not!

74
00:05:25,280 --> 00:05:26,760
It's not theft or anything like that.

75
00:05:27,040 --> 00:05:28,080
Patience, my Lord

76
00:05:29,280 --> 00:05:30,320
Look at me, Haydar!

77
00:05:30,760 --> 00:05:32,200
They humiliate us every day.

78
00:05:32,640 --> 00:05:35,720
They didn't leave us alone,
saying they'd pay off our debt

79
00:05:37,560 --> 00:05:39,000
If they’ve brought us to this state,

80
00:05:39,800 --> 00:05:41,360
of course there would be a price to pay

81
00:05:42,800 --> 00:05:43,839
Look!

82
00:05:43,840 --> 00:05:45,760
Every day, millions are
flowing into the company

83
00:05:45,880 --> 00:05:47,600
but not a penny reaches our hands.

84
00:05:48,520 --> 00:05:51,480
What's more, our daughter
works day and night

85
00:05:53,080 --> 00:05:54,879
Alright, you can take that mindset.

86
00:05:54,880 --> 00:05:56,200
But I won't! Do you understand?

87
00:05:56,240 --> 00:05:58,560
Alright, alright. Shut up, for God's sake.

88
00:06:01,320 --> 00:06:03,800
So Honestly, I give up Nermin, I give up!

89
00:06:05,840 --> 00:06:08,720
Alright, if Müzeyyen finds out about
this, she'll tear the place apart.

90
00:06:08,840 --> 00:06:10,200
Don't involve me in this.

91
00:06:10,400 --> 00:06:11,440
Don't you dare!

92
00:06:12,760 --> 00:06:13,800
Honestly, my dear

93
00:06:15,200 --> 00:06:17,600
Since you're my husband,
you'll naturally get involved.

94
00:06:18,680 --> 00:06:20,640
If Müzeyyen the witch finds out,

95
00:06:21,240 --> 00:06:22,680
we'll pay her and that'll be that

96
00:06:24,320 --> 00:06:28,640
If not, they would make up for the
money they made off Mercan's back.

97
00:06:30,480 --> 00:06:32,560
I'm just getting by
thinking I'm clever, you know?

98
00:06:33,040 --> 00:06:35,040
Get rid of these already!

99
00:06:35,080 --> 00:06:36,080
Time to sleep.

100
00:06:38,120 --> 00:06:39,159
Beautiful!

101
00:06:39,160 --> 00:06:40,160
I'm glad I bought it.

102
00:06:44,800 --> 00:06:46,080
What type of situation we're in!

103
00:07:12,880 --> 00:07:15,360
Oh, dear! What did you do my
darling? Don't you pay attention?

104
00:07:17,040 --> 00:07:18,880
Stop, stop! Don't pick
it up with your hands.

105
00:07:19,720 --> 00:07:20,880
I said don't touch it.

106
00:07:21,080 --> 00:07:22,440
We needed a broom or something...

107
00:07:22,480 --> 00:07:23,480
Oh my goodness!

108
00:07:23,680 --> 00:07:24,720
Does it hurt?

109
00:07:26,640 --> 00:07:29,800
Wait. I'll get you a bandage
right away, wait, does it hurt?

110
00:07:29,920 --> 00:07:31,400
It's not my hand that's hurting, Mum.

111
00:07:33,800 --> 00:07:34,960
It is my heart!

112
00:07:36,400 --> 00:07:37,560
It hurts so bad in my heart.

113
00:07:49,840 --> 00:07:50,880
Mom.

114
00:07:51,480 --> 00:07:53,760
Sorry, I didn't mean to say that

115
00:07:56,400 --> 00:07:57,440
Come here.

116
00:08:00,280 --> 00:08:01,280
It hurts, right?

117
00:08:01,520 --> 00:08:02,520
Yes.

118
00:08:04,480 --> 00:08:07,080
Oh, my little girl!

119
00:08:08,000 --> 00:08:09,160
Hold on, I am covering it.

120
00:08:20,840 --> 00:08:22,840
Oh, my little girl!

121
00:08:29,800 --> 00:08:31,040
Take it, you use it later.

122
00:08:32,440 --> 00:08:33,480
No need.

123
00:08:53,440 --> 00:08:54,480
What is this?

124
00:09:10,320 --> 00:09:11,400
Come on! You can do it.

125
00:09:19,840 --> 00:09:22,519
There's this missing piece, and
it just doesn't sit right with me.

126
00:09:22,520 --> 00:09:24,160
Take a look at this.

127
00:09:29,520 --> 00:09:30,600
I think it's fine.

128
00:09:33,840 --> 00:09:35,640
No way, that wont work.

129
00:09:36,320 --> 00:09:39,120
There's no need to send it,
there's really no need at all. Really.

130
00:09:39,160 --> 00:09:40,760
It just won't work.

131
00:09:42,640 --> 00:09:43,880
Don't get discouraged.

132
00:09:44,640 --> 00:09:45,880
Nothing is wrong, believe me.

133
00:09:48,520 --> 00:09:50,000
It feels like we're pushing ourselves

134
00:09:50,200 --> 00:09:51,600
as if our minds are all messed up.

135
00:09:52,040 --> 00:09:53,840
I just can't figure
out why it's not working.

136
00:09:54,840 --> 00:09:57,120
As if there is a much different
world on the other side,

137
00:09:57,520 --> 00:09:59,640
while the outside world is full of chaos.

138
00:10:00,400 --> 00:10:02,919
It's not working out, we're
just pushing ourselves for nothing.

139
00:10:02,920 --> 00:10:04,840
We don't have to conform
to the outside world.

140
00:10:05,160 --> 00:10:06,360
But we can't ignore it either.

141
00:10:07,400 --> 00:10:09,720
Like... one thing on the
inside and another on the outside

142
00:10:09,840 --> 00:10:12,319
No, best not to push it. Let's
not send it. I'm giving up.

143
00:10:12,320 --> 00:10:13,840
Wait a minute.

144
00:10:19,240 --> 00:10:20,320
Take a deep breath.

145
00:10:21,400 --> 00:10:22,440
I said take it!

146
00:10:24,360 --> 00:10:25,400
Give it now.

147
00:10:28,600 --> 00:10:29,600
Close your eyes.

148
00:10:32,400 --> 00:10:33,400
Close them!

149
00:10:55,560 --> 00:10:56,640
No cheating!

150
00:10:57,120 --> 00:10:58,120
Eyes closed.

151
00:11:04,600 --> 00:11:05,680
Take a deep breath.

152
00:11:07,400 --> 00:11:08,480
Now give it.

153
00:11:18,840 --> 00:11:19,880
One more time.

154
00:11:28,760 --> 00:11:29,760
Don't open your eyes.

155
00:11:30,760 --> 00:11:31,800
Trust me.

156
00:11:33,480 --> 00:11:34,480
And if you wish,

157
00:11:35,920 --> 00:11:37,600
We can leave everything behind right now.

158
00:11:38,160 --> 00:11:39,240
Everything.

159
00:11:39,640 --> 00:11:40,959
If you say "Just don't push it"

160
00:11:40,960 --> 00:11:42,080
everything comes to an end.

161
00:11:42,800 --> 00:11:44,200
However, if we keep going

162
00:11:44,760 --> 00:11:46,480
something great could come out of it.

163
00:11:48,160 --> 00:11:49,360
You never know until you try.

164
00:11:58,120 --> 00:11:59,120
I understand your fears.

165
00:12:00,240 --> 00:12:01,240
I'm not sure either.

166
00:12:02,320 --> 00:12:04,160
But in such a short time

167
00:12:04,720 --> 00:12:06,680
There may be an mistake
in what we trying to do.

168
00:12:08,680 --> 00:12:09,720
Anyways,

169
00:12:10,160 --> 00:12:13,840
If it were flawless and smooth,
perhaps it wouldn't be so valuable.

170
00:12:18,160 --> 00:12:20,000
There should be a trace
of us in the building.

171
00:12:20,480 --> 00:12:21,520
A line,

172
00:12:21,960 --> 00:12:23,760
I don't know, a crooked stone.

173
00:12:24,960 --> 00:12:26,840
A feeling from us in its own world.

174
00:12:28,320 --> 00:12:29,760
It will stand firm there.

175
00:12:31,520 --> 00:12:32,600
I don't know

176
00:12:32,800 --> 00:12:35,400
Perhaps, what you call “inside
one thing, outside another” is

177
00:12:35,840 --> 00:12:36,880
something deep within,

178
00:12:37,240 --> 00:12:39,480
we haven't yet revealed to the outside

179
00:12:39,560 --> 00:12:41,640
Perhaps, it is something

180
00:12:42,320 --> 00:12:44,160
we have yet to discover.

181
00:12:52,600 --> 00:12:53,600
And perhaps,

182
00:12:54,200 --> 00:12:55,440
we'll be the ones who find it.

183
00:12:56,920 --> 00:12:57,960
Who knows

184
00:13:10,160 --> 00:13:12,760
We can't know what will happen
until it comes to light, can we?

185
00:13:14,360 --> 00:13:15,560
Everything is in our hands.

186
00:13:23,600 --> 00:13:24,640
It's worth a try then.

187
00:13:26,560 --> 00:13:27,760
Well, let's get back to work.

188
00:13:29,080 --> 00:13:30,080
Come on.

189
00:13:31,200 --> 00:13:32,560
What are you looking at? Come on!

190
00:13:32,600 --> 00:13:33,600
We'll make it.

191
00:14:26,480 --> 00:14:27,520
Hello, Aslı, my daughter,

192
00:14:28,800 --> 00:14:30,240
Did you take my necklace?

193
00:14:30,960 --> 00:14:32,240
I can't find my necklace.

194
00:14:34,920 --> 00:14:37,720
I looked there darling, I turned
the room upside down. it's not there.

195
00:14:38,240 --> 00:14:39,280
Alright, fine.

196
00:14:39,880 --> 00:14:42,720
I'll ask Zehra, that scatterbrain
may have put it somewhere else.

197
00:14:45,800 --> 00:14:46,800
Zehra!

198
00:14:47,560 --> 00:14:48,600
Zehra!

199
00:15:00,640 --> 00:15:01,680
Come in!

200
00:15:03,120 --> 00:15:04,240
Yes, Mrs. Müzeyyen.

201
00:15:08,040 --> 00:15:09,680
Zehra, I can't find my necklace.

202
00:15:10,280 --> 00:15:11,400
Do you know where it is?

203
00:15:23,280 --> 00:15:24,280
No.

204
00:15:27,600 --> 00:15:29,440
I never touch the jewellery box.

205
00:15:29,680 --> 00:15:31,480
I don't even open the drawer, Mrs Müzeyyen.

206
00:15:38,640 --> 00:15:40,720
Tell Binnaz and Çiçek
to wait for me downstairs.

207
00:15:46,240 --> 00:15:48,040
Whoever dared to do this

208
00:15:48,400 --> 00:15:50,200
I'll give them a hard time.

209
00:15:51,000 --> 00:15:52,040
A very hard time.

210
00:15:55,240 --> 00:15:56,240
I 've sent it.

211
00:16:01,120 --> 00:16:02,400
Well done, everyone!

212
00:16:02,760 --> 00:16:04,880
We worked hard. We worked
hard, but it was worth it.

213
00:16:10,640 --> 00:16:12,280
Thank you all very much.

214
00:16:12,480 --> 00:16:14,080
We worked hard and we deserved it.

215
00:16:14,720 --> 00:16:16,560
Now you can go home and take a rest.

216
00:16:17,600 --> 00:16:19,360
Because in the evening, you are invited to

217
00:16:19,520 --> 00:16:21,040
the barbecue party at the mansion.

218
00:16:21,720 --> 00:16:22,720
Super!
Yay!

219
00:16:30,160 --> 00:16:31,840
That's great.

220
00:16:32,160 --> 00:16:33,320
We deserved it.

221
00:16:34,600 --> 00:16:36,200
I'm glad you didn't let me give up.

222
00:16:37,360 --> 00:16:40,000
Even if you had wanted to give
up, no one could have stopped you.

223
00:16:40,840 --> 00:16:41,920
Not even I.

224
00:16:43,000 --> 00:16:44,560
I'll take that as a compliment then.

225
00:16:45,520 --> 00:16:46,920
Whatever you say.

226
00:16:50,120 --> 00:16:52,040
If we win this project

227
00:16:52,680 --> 00:16:54,280
there will be a trace of us in it.

228
00:16:56,560 --> 00:16:57,760
A crooked stone

229
00:16:58,600 --> 00:16:59,680
ordinary

230
00:16:59,800 --> 00:17:00,880
shapeless

231
00:17:02,760 --> 00:17:05,080
Perhaps I'll come across it
while walking down the street

232
00:17:06,040 --> 00:17:07,120
But that stone

233
00:17:07,360 --> 00:17:09,320
will be the most valuable
stone of the project.

234
00:17:10,920 --> 00:17:11,960
Yes.

235
00:17:14,840 --> 00:17:15,920
Mr. Ateş,

236
00:17:17,920 --> 00:17:18,960
You're well

237
00:17:19,040 --> 00:17:20,080
I hope.

238
00:17:21,560 --> 00:17:22,560
Well, I

239
00:17:23,720 --> 00:17:24,800
I wanted to ask something

240
00:17:27,720 --> 00:17:29,200
Am I invited too?

241
00:17:29,240 --> 00:17:30,320
To the barbecue?

242
00:17:31,040 --> 00:17:33,120
Cause I worked very hard
too, I think I deserved it.

243
00:17:42,480 --> 00:17:44,080
Of course you are invited, Yaşar.

244
00:17:46,320 --> 00:17:48,560
I'll make you an olive
pizza with my own hands.

245
00:17:51,160 --> 00:17:52,240
Live it up, Mr. Ateş!

246
00:17:57,840 --> 00:17:58,840
Thank you.

247
00:18:04,680 --> 00:18:05,680
Shall we go?

248
00:18:06,040 --> 00:18:07,120
Let's go!

249
00:18:31,360 --> 00:18:33,040
Zehra, what are you doing?

250
00:18:33,720 --> 00:18:34,960
It just came out of the oven.

251
00:18:35,120 --> 00:18:36,200
It will become doughy!

252
00:18:36,480 --> 00:18:38,280
Haven't you ever learned anything?

253
00:18:38,840 --> 00:18:39,880
Meddlesome.

254
00:18:48,440 --> 00:18:49,480
What happened now?

255
00:18:50,480 --> 00:18:51,520
I don't know.

256
00:18:53,720 --> 00:18:55,440
It's clear that nothing good has happened.

257
00:19:06,840 --> 00:19:08,280
Who entered my room yesterday?

258
00:19:11,240 --> 00:19:14,120
I was in the kitchen
all day, Mrs. Müzeyyen.

259
00:19:14,840 --> 00:19:17,280
And I helped my mother, I
didn't go into your room at all.

260
00:19:18,760 --> 00:19:19,760
My necklace is missing.

261
00:19:20,240 --> 00:19:21,600
Whoever took it should speak up.

262
00:19:32,640 --> 00:19:34,280
We're not thieves, Mrs. Müzeyyen.

263
00:19:35,640 --> 00:19:37,879
Don't try to use that “poor
man's speech” stuff on me.

264
00:19:37,880 --> 00:19:39,200
Someone has entered my room.

265
00:19:40,000 --> 00:19:43,240
There's no one else in this house who
could have come into my room, except you.

266
00:19:43,680 --> 00:19:45,040
Don't make me lose my temper.

267
00:19:45,960 --> 00:19:48,400
Whoever took it, tell me
quickly or I'll call the police.

268
00:19:49,840 --> 00:19:51,760
You'd better call the
police, Mrs. Müzeyyen.

269
00:19:53,680 --> 00:19:54,880
That's the right thing to do.

270
00:19:56,920 --> 00:19:58,200
We won't enter your room

271
00:19:59,240 --> 00:20:01,000
Zehra is responsible for your room.

272
00:20:01,400 --> 00:20:04,240
It was never us who manage your room.

273
00:20:14,520 --> 00:20:15,600
What's going on here?

274
00:20:16,200 --> 00:20:18,160
Mrs. Müzeyyen's necklace is missing.

275
00:20:35,800 --> 00:20:36,840
What happened?

276
00:20:36,880 --> 00:20:37,920
What's all this abundance?

277
00:20:38,640 --> 00:20:39,760
Did you find a treasure?

278
00:20:41,880 --> 00:20:43,920
We don't die easily, Mrs. Müzeyyen.

279
00:20:48,040 --> 00:20:49,120
What happened?

280
00:20:49,440 --> 00:20:51,120
What is the source of all these?

281
00:20:54,000 --> 00:20:55,120
Did you find the treasure?

282
00:20:56,200 --> 00:20:57,280
Or did you steal?

283
00:21:06,920 --> 00:21:07,920
You stole it!

284
00:21:12,200 --> 00:21:13,320
Good heavens!

285
00:21:14,560 --> 00:21:16,360
Why would I steal your necklace, dear?

286
00:21:19,960 --> 00:21:22,920
If stones were to rain down on our
heads, you'd still put the blame on us.

287
00:21:23,320 --> 00:21:24,320
Unbelievable!

288
00:21:28,680 --> 00:21:30,120
Everyone back to work!

289
00:22:18,320 --> 00:22:19,840
It is time to go shopping.

290
00:22:23,440 --> 00:22:25,880
I haven't hosted my
colleagues in a long time.

291
00:22:27,040 --> 00:22:28,400
Even after getting married...

292
00:22:30,640 --> 00:22:31,720
What were you going to say?

293
00:22:33,080 --> 00:22:34,080
Nothing.

294
00:22:35,520 --> 00:22:37,639
You were going to say that
we couldn't invite anyone

295
00:22:37,640 --> 00:22:39,080
after we got married, weren't you?

296
00:22:39,960 --> 00:22:40,960
So

297
00:22:41,120 --> 00:22:43,360
Considering the circumstances
under which we got married

298
00:22:43,840 --> 00:22:44,880
it seems normal.

299
00:22:45,720 --> 00:22:46,960
But let's look at the present.

300
00:22:47,320 --> 00:22:50,199
They'll be here in a few hours and
we haven't made any preparations yet.

301
00:22:50,200 --> 00:22:51,880
Alright. Don't worry.

302
00:22:52,040 --> 00:22:54,520
Now make a list and tell
Berat. He will handle it.

303
00:22:55,920 --> 00:22:57,680
I want everything to be perfect.

304
00:22:58,480 --> 00:22:59,720
So until morning

305
00:22:59,760 --> 00:23:01,080
They worked diligently.

306
00:23:01,280 --> 00:23:04,040
We neglected our work and made
them pay the price in the end.

307
00:23:05,360 --> 00:23:06,440
I will make up for it.

308
00:23:06,720 --> 00:23:07,760
Don't worry.

309
00:23:10,120 --> 00:23:12,440
We need to prepare something
besides meat and chicken.

310
00:23:14,640 --> 00:23:15,720
Alright.

311
00:23:15,920 --> 00:23:17,240
Like... plenty of sweets

312
00:23:17,320 --> 00:23:18,360
drinks and such

313
00:23:19,240 --> 00:23:20,240
Alright.

314
00:23:23,840 --> 00:23:25,360
Let's cook some venison shwarma too.

315
00:23:26,960 --> 00:23:28,040
Alright.

316
00:23:30,800 --> 00:23:32,000
Aren't you listening to me?

317
00:23:34,120 --> 00:23:35,160
Of course I'm listening.

318
00:23:36,440 --> 00:23:38,440
I just said "Let's cook
some venison shwarma too".

319
00:23:41,200 --> 00:23:42,200
Did you really say that?

320
00:23:44,720 --> 00:23:46,280
Oh, come on, really?

321
00:23:46,760 --> 00:23:49,440
I'm trying to tell you something
here, our guests are about to come

322
00:23:49,480 --> 00:23:51,840
and you're just brushing
it off with a 'yes'.

323
00:23:54,200 --> 00:23:55,480
It's because I trust you.

324
00:23:56,560 --> 00:23:58,640
I know you'll organise it perfectly.

325
00:24:00,440 --> 00:24:01,520
Whatever you say is okay.

326
00:24:03,960 --> 00:24:05,440
Did I earn your appreciation then?

327
00:24:07,520 --> 00:24:08,600
Lucky me!

328
00:24:10,000 --> 00:24:11,000
But first

329
00:24:12,000 --> 00:24:13,000
Go to your room

330
00:24:13,240 --> 00:24:14,320
Take some rest.

331
00:24:14,440 --> 00:24:16,520
After all, there are a
bunch of employees at home.

332
00:24:16,560 --> 00:24:17,759
They take care of everything.

333
00:24:17,760 --> 00:24:19,160
Then you'll do what you have to do.

334
00:24:19,200 --> 00:24:22,800
I'm not sleepy, I need to
get the arbor ready first.

335
00:24:24,680 --> 00:24:26,640
No matter what I say,
you won't listen, right?

336
00:24:56,560 --> 00:24:58,640
It's time to put an end to things.

337
00:25:18,440 --> 00:25:19,479
What happened, my dear?

338
00:25:19,480 --> 00:25:22,000
Why are you looking so down?

339
00:25:22,040 --> 00:25:24,416
Can't you see Mrs. Müzeyyen
She has driven me mad, you know.

340
00:25:24,440 --> 00:25:25,480
What happened?

341
00:25:25,520 --> 00:25:28,280
Her necklace is missing. She
gave all of us a good dressing-down.

342
00:25:28,320 --> 00:25:29,920
She is anew money. What do we expect?

343
00:25:31,040 --> 00:25:32,040
What do you mean?

344
00:25:32,280 --> 00:25:33,360
Did she accuse you?

345
00:25:34,240 --> 00:25:35,800
Isn't it always like that anyway?

346
00:25:36,080 --> 00:25:37,880
First, the household staff are blamed.

347
00:25:39,720 --> 00:25:40,760
I can't believe it

348
00:25:45,200 --> 00:25:46,240
My dear,

349
00:25:46,320 --> 00:25:48,280
I'm so sorry that you
had to go through all that.

350
00:25:50,640 --> 00:25:52,880
Don't worry, everything
will work out in time.

351
00:25:53,520 --> 00:25:55,040
Well, I don't really care about her.

352
00:25:56,640 --> 00:25:58,840
It's my mother's silence that scares me.

353
00:25:59,320 --> 00:26:01,200
This is not a good sign, Malik.

354
00:26:01,480 --> 00:26:03,320
She hasn't said a word in two days.

355
00:26:04,040 --> 00:26:05,160
She might be softening up?

356
00:26:06,320 --> 00:26:07,560
I wish that were the case

357
00:26:09,360 --> 00:26:11,080
but she doesn't bring anything out either.

358
00:26:12,080 --> 00:26:13,480
II'll get everything back on track.

359
00:26:14,080 --> 00:26:15,080
I promise you.

360
00:26:16,720 --> 00:26:18,360
Don't you worry so much anymore.

361
00:26:18,800 --> 00:26:20,080
Don't get upset, okay?

362
00:26:24,600 --> 00:26:26,600
I can't help but worry.

363
00:26:27,160 --> 00:26:28,480
It's not that easy.

364
00:26:29,040 --> 00:26:30,040
Yeah, it's not easy.

365
00:26:31,120 --> 00:26:32,560
But it's not that difficult either.

366
00:26:37,040 --> 00:26:39,720
Çiçek, I cannot let you to go anywhere.

367
00:26:41,080 --> 00:26:42,080
I can't bear it.

368
00:27:05,160 --> 00:27:06,240
One for you,

369
00:27:06,280 --> 00:27:07,320
and one for me.

370
00:27:08,600 --> 00:27:09,679
Thank you.

371
00:27:09,680 --> 00:27:10,720
Enjoy it.

372
00:27:15,680 --> 00:27:16,760
Between you and Burak,

373
00:27:17,120 --> 00:27:19,360
There's a distance now
because of your brother, right?

374
00:27:21,080 --> 00:27:22,080
Yes.

375
00:27:24,640 --> 00:27:26,680
I liked Burak's friends

376
00:27:27,880 --> 00:27:30,720
I got very upset when I drifted
away because of my brother.

377
00:27:34,000 --> 00:27:36,040
We worked very well together.

378
00:27:39,760 --> 00:27:42,920
Did you just like his friendship, Demet?

379
00:27:46,840 --> 00:27:47,840
Um,

380
00:27:49,440 --> 00:27:50,520
I don't know.

381
00:27:52,720 --> 00:27:54,200
My feelings are all over the place.

382
00:27:56,480 --> 00:27:58,200
I can't put a name to what I'm feeling.

383
00:28:00,200 --> 00:28:01,480
I always want to be with him

384
00:28:02,440 --> 00:28:03,920
and always to talk to him.

385
00:28:10,400 --> 00:28:11,760
When he stay away from me

386
00:28:14,200 --> 00:28:15,520
it hurts me so much.

387
00:28:17,640 --> 00:28:20,960
Might that thing you can not name be

388
00:28:21,560 --> 00:28:22,640
love?

389
00:28:29,040 --> 00:28:30,120
Perhaps.

390
00:28:33,800 --> 00:28:35,920
I'm feeling this way about
someone for the first time

391
00:29:46,360 --> 00:29:47,680
I'd say "may it be easy," but...

392
00:29:48,640 --> 00:29:49,680
Zehra would handle it.

393
00:29:50,120 --> 00:29:51,280
You're being stubborn again.

394
00:29:52,920 --> 00:29:53,920
I'm handling it.

395
00:29:54,760 --> 00:29:56,320
After all, they're already very busy.

396
00:29:58,000 --> 00:29:59,360
In fact, I enjoy doing it.

397
00:30:01,280 --> 00:30:02,320
Let me help too.

398
00:30:02,960 --> 00:30:03,960
No, no need.

399
00:30:05,800 --> 00:30:07,360
Don't put me off by chatting away now.

400
00:30:07,440 --> 00:30:08,800
I need to get my work done.

401
00:30:10,200 --> 00:30:11,280
Okay.

402
00:30:11,360 --> 00:30:13,040
Then I'll sit here and watch you.

403
00:30:14,320 --> 00:30:16,160
It will be enjoyable to watch your efforts.

404
00:30:19,640 --> 00:30:20,680
That's very rude.

405
00:30:21,200 --> 00:30:23,040
I don't want to get
distracted because of you.

406
00:30:28,800 --> 00:30:30,040
Am I distracting you?

407
00:30:33,320 --> 00:30:35,600
No, I mean, what I meant to say was...

408
00:30:36,200 --> 00:30:37,240
No matter who

409
00:30:37,480 --> 00:30:38,560
it would be like that.

410
00:30:39,920 --> 00:30:43,480
I'm telling you, don't chat away.
You keep chatting, putting me off.

411
00:31:12,160 --> 00:31:14,360
This cover doesn't
really match the service.

412
00:31:15,080 --> 00:31:16,520
They contrast with each other.

413
00:31:17,440 --> 00:31:18,440
Aren't they?

414
00:31:21,120 --> 00:31:22,200
I think they match.

415
00:31:26,520 --> 00:31:28,080
Contrast is not a flaw.

416
00:31:30,560 --> 00:31:31,640
Of course not.

417
00:31:31,720 --> 00:31:32,920
I didn't say it was a flaw.

418
00:31:35,000 --> 00:31:36,040
I don't know.

419
00:31:38,800 --> 00:31:41,480
Well, when you look at it like
that, it actually looks quite nice.

420
00:31:44,760 --> 00:31:46,000
It seems to be pulling you in.

421
00:31:47,320 --> 00:31:48,920
They're happy to be together.

422
00:31:51,720 --> 00:31:52,800
I think they are happy too

423
00:31:57,280 --> 00:31:58,280
One has the chaos,

424
00:32:00,160 --> 00:32:01,440
and the other has the serenity.

425
00:32:03,120 --> 00:32:04,920
They would disappear if they were the same.

426
00:32:06,560 --> 00:32:08,000
But they draw attention this way.

427
00:32:09,840 --> 00:32:11,800
As if without one,

428
00:32:12,040 --> 00:32:14,200
the other would not exist.

429
00:32:23,640 --> 00:32:25,320
What did I do with the forks and knives?

430
00:32:27,280 --> 00:32:28,320
Oh my God.

431
00:32:31,960 --> 00:32:34,040
Çiçek had brought them here but...

432
00:32:36,120 --> 00:32:37,120
They're over there.

433
00:32:40,160 --> 00:32:41,200
Correct.

434
00:32:47,760 --> 00:32:48,880
I've forgotten about them.

435
00:32:49,880 --> 00:32:51,920
I'm human too, after all.
I might forget, Mr Ateş.

436
00:32:53,160 --> 00:32:54,160
Of course, of course.

437
00:32:54,800 --> 00:32:55,800
Mrs. Mercan.

438
00:33:02,520 --> 00:33:04,120
Wait a minute, let me tell you something

439
00:33:05,360 --> 00:33:06,400
Come with me.

440
00:33:10,160 --> 00:33:11,160
Could you

441
00:33:11,280 --> 00:33:13,480
arrange these decorations, please?

442
00:33:13,960 --> 00:33:16,120
You know these are heavy,
I'd rather not carry these.

443
00:33:16,160 --> 00:33:17,160
Of course.

444
00:33:20,800 --> 00:33:21,840
Where should I leave it?

445
00:33:22,280 --> 00:33:23,320
I think here

446
00:33:23,440 --> 00:33:25,040
could be okay. The corner on the right.

447
00:33:29,200 --> 00:33:30,280
Is this okay?

448
00:33:31,840 --> 00:33:33,080
No, there are no bushes there.

449
00:33:33,360 --> 00:33:34,640
Could you take it to the left?

450
00:33:40,560 --> 00:33:41,560
Move forward a little.

451
00:33:49,120 --> 00:33:50,320
Can I put it? Is it good here?

452
00:33:51,960 --> 00:33:53,040
No, it's not.

453
00:33:54,040 --> 00:33:55,040
Look, geet it over there.

454
00:33:56,840 --> 00:33:57,920
God give me patience!

455
00:33:59,280 --> 00:34:00,560
You said you'd help me

456
00:34:00,760 --> 00:34:01,840
Why are you complainingnow?

457
00:34:02,720 --> 00:34:03,960
Decide already.

458
00:34:04,040 --> 00:34:05,480
I'll end up with a hernia otherwise.

459
00:34:06,480 --> 00:34:07,680
Alright, alright, leave it.

460
00:34:08,120 --> 00:34:09,120
God forbid.

461
00:34:09,160 --> 00:34:10,160
This is a good spot.

462
00:34:11,720 --> 00:34:12,800
Are you okay?

463
00:34:13,080 --> 00:34:14,160
I don't think so.

464
00:34:22,440 --> 00:34:23,560
I think I fooled you.

465
00:34:27,040 --> 00:34:28,080
You're so bad.

466
00:34:28,640 --> 00:34:29,720
I was losing my mind.

467
00:34:31,080 --> 00:34:32,480
If you keep tormenting me like this

468
00:34:32,840 --> 00:34:34,120
you'll get what's coming to you.

469
00:34:39,800 --> 00:34:40,800
Did you get terrified?

470
00:34:43,720 --> 00:34:46,320
I don't want anyone to get
hurt because of me, that's all.

471
00:34:51,480 --> 00:34:53,240
Should we bring the chairs?

472
00:34:57,080 --> 00:34:59,120
They won't get cold, don't worry.

473
00:35:01,920 --> 00:35:02,920
Don't look like that.

474
00:35:03,640 --> 00:35:06,800
I haven't forgotten you said "Your name
is fire that's why you won't get cold"

475
00:35:11,320 --> 00:35:12,320
You're right.

476
00:35:13,400 --> 00:35:15,000
I suppose so, chairs are good this way.

477
00:35:15,400 --> 00:35:16,440
Nice.

478
00:35:20,080 --> 00:35:21,360
How quickly you were convinced.

479
00:35:23,920 --> 00:35:24,960
You're right.

480
00:35:25,680 --> 00:35:28,800
I like it too, it's simple and not flashy.

481
00:35:29,920 --> 00:35:31,000
Like a family atmosphere.

482
00:35:31,600 --> 00:35:33,520
Colleagues are considered
a part of our family

483
00:35:35,840 --> 00:35:37,720
so they need to feel
comfortable at our home.

484
00:35:41,480 --> 00:35:42,520
Our home?

485
00:35:43,960 --> 00:35:47,200
She said our home.

486
00:35:49,720 --> 00:35:50,720
You're right.

487
00:35:51,720 --> 00:35:52,800
At our house

488
00:35:53,360 --> 00:35:54,560
they should feel comfortable.

489
00:36:00,040 --> 00:36:01,760
I'd better continue to the table.

490
00:36:08,320 --> 00:36:09,520
Shall I go and check on Cemal?

491
00:36:11,600 --> 00:36:12,679
Of course, of course.

492
00:36:12,680 --> 00:36:13,760
Go check him.

493
00:36:13,800 --> 00:36:14,800
Go.

494
00:36:31,960 --> 00:36:34,000
What happened now? I am
saying "our home" and such?

495
00:36:36,800 --> 00:36:37,880
What's happening, Mercan?

496
00:36:52,640 --> 00:36:53,680
Put yourself together.

497
00:36:54,760 --> 00:36:55,760
Put yourself together.

498
00:36:56,000 --> 00:36:57,000
Mercan!

499
00:36:58,880 --> 00:36:59,960
I've put it wrong.

500
00:37:08,080 --> 00:37:09,880
Are you sure you've looked everywhere?

501
00:37:10,200 --> 00:37:11,240
I did, my dear.

502
00:37:11,680 --> 00:37:13,920
I turned the whole room
upside down, but it's not there.

503
00:37:14,240 --> 00:37:15,560
It was there, in the box.

504
00:37:20,440 --> 00:37:21,480
What are you doing?

505
00:37:21,840 --> 00:37:23,600
I'm calling the police. If it's stolen...

506
00:37:24,920 --> 00:37:26,000
Don't be ridiculous.

507
00:37:26,160 --> 00:37:27,160
There's no need.

508
00:37:27,400 --> 00:37:29,040
Besides, I know who took it.

509
00:37:30,280 --> 00:37:31,319
How?

510
00:37:31,320 --> 00:37:32,320
You know?

511
00:37:32,680 --> 00:37:33,760
Who took it, Mum?

512
00:37:35,000 --> 00:37:36,040
Nermin.

513
00:37:41,240 --> 00:37:43,879
She went on a shopping spree
even though she didn't have a penny.

514
00:37:43,880 --> 00:37:45,120
All of them were branded items.

515
00:37:47,480 --> 00:37:48,800
What are you waiting for then?

516
00:37:49,320 --> 00:37:50,360
Go talk to her!

517
00:37:50,400 --> 00:37:51,400
Confront her!

518
00:37:54,400 --> 00:37:56,320
If necessary, report her to the police.

519
00:37:56,880 --> 00:37:58,960
We can even throw those
scumbags to the press.

520
00:38:00,600 --> 00:38:01,680
No.

521
00:38:01,880 --> 00:38:03,480
I need to prove it first.

522
00:38:06,120 --> 00:38:07,320
If I make a wrong move

523
00:38:07,920 --> 00:38:09,800
In the eyes of Ateş,
Nermin will be the victim,

524
00:38:09,840 --> 00:38:11,840
and I will become the guilty one.

525
00:38:14,400 --> 00:38:16,440
But I'll catch her at just the right moment

526
00:38:17,000 --> 00:38:18,520
so she'll never be able to deny it.

527
00:38:18,680 --> 00:38:19,680
Don't worry about it.

528
00:38:23,680 --> 00:38:24,720
Just think about it

529
00:38:25,920 --> 00:38:28,720
Her daughter is wandering
around as if she is a princess.

530
00:38:29,840 --> 00:38:31,480
But her mother is actually a thief.

531
00:38:36,120 --> 00:38:39,480
I'd like to see Mercan's face
when this comes out, to be honest.

532
00:38:41,680 --> 00:38:42,680
We'll see.

533
00:39:18,600 --> 00:39:19,680
It turned out very well.

534
00:39:30,960 --> 00:39:33,920
I see you've really gotten
caught up in the marriage game

535
00:39:37,960 --> 00:39:40,080
Do you really think you
can pull Ateş like that?

536
00:39:42,000 --> 00:39:43,200
You're really stupid.

537
00:39:56,760 --> 00:39:58,080
What do you think you're doing?

538
00:39:58,920 --> 00:40:00,000
Look at these.

539
00:40:00,600 --> 00:40:01,800
You really have a poor taste.

540
00:40:02,880 --> 00:40:03,959
Those flowers

541
00:40:03,960 --> 00:40:05,040
and so on

542
00:40:05,400 --> 00:40:06,520
looks miserable.

543
00:40:19,720 --> 00:40:21,800
What are you doing?

544
00:40:24,320 --> 00:40:25,640
Can't you tell what I'm doing?

545
00:40:29,120 --> 00:40:31,840
I'm saving you from embarrassing
yourself in front of your guests.

546
00:40:34,080 --> 00:40:36,200
You're mad.

547
00:40:36,760 --> 00:40:37,760
Aslıhan!

548
00:40:43,040 --> 00:40:44,040
What are you doing?

549
00:40:45,480 --> 00:40:46,560
Nothing.

550
00:40:46,920 --> 00:40:48,440
She is a little bit clumsy, I guess.

551
00:40:48,520 --> 00:40:49,600
She dropped all of them.

552
00:40:51,120 --> 00:40:53,120
Oh, my god!

553
00:40:53,160 --> 00:40:54,280
I am going to lose my mind.

554
00:41:03,520 --> 00:41:04,600
Don't be upset.

555
00:41:04,640 --> 00:41:05,880
We'll sort it out together now

556
00:41:06,400 --> 00:41:07,520
No need, I'll handle it.

557
00:41:07,760 --> 00:41:09,200
I didn't ask if you could handle it.

558
00:41:09,880 --> 00:41:10,920
Come on, don't dawdle.

559
00:42:11,080 --> 00:42:13,840
I learned that Ateş had a
brother and he died, Ziya.

560
00:42:14,720 --> 00:42:15,760
Find out for me

561
00:42:15,800 --> 00:42:16,880
what is his brother's name

562
00:42:16,960 --> 00:42:18,640
why he died and where his grave is.

563
00:42:19,120 --> 00:42:20,200
I need this information.

564
00:42:20,600 --> 00:42:23,160
Perhaps, this way we can
learn something about Ateş.

565
00:42:24,040 --> 00:42:26,760
I'll take the money
upfront, Haydar, my brother.

566
00:42:27,000 --> 00:42:29,680
My men don't take a step without payment.

567
00:42:35,400 --> 00:42:37,480
Did you think I'll get a
job done without payment?

568
00:42:38,600 --> 00:42:39,680
Look.

569
00:42:44,200 --> 00:42:46,960
They say, “Even if you find it on
the road, you'd better count it.”

570
00:42:47,520 --> 00:42:49,240
You can presume this job is done already.

571
00:42:49,480 --> 00:42:50,920
Bring me this information, Ziya.

572
00:42:51,360 --> 00:42:52,400
It's very important.

573
00:42:52,520 --> 00:42:53,840
It is a matter of life and death.

574
00:42:54,600 --> 00:42:55,760
I'll pay you double.

575
00:42:57,400 --> 00:42:58,480
Alright.

576
00:42:59,640 --> 00:43:00,680
I'll take care of this.

577
00:43:43,840 --> 00:43:44,840
Berat!

578
00:43:46,720 --> 00:43:48,200
What are you doing here?

579
00:43:51,440 --> 00:43:52,879
You don't even answer my calls.

580
00:43:52,880 --> 00:43:54,320
Are you avoiding me?

581
00:43:54,560 --> 00:43:55,560
Huh?

582
00:43:55,600 --> 00:43:56,760
Baby, no. I'm working.

583
00:43:56,920 --> 00:43:57,920
Don't you see?
Come here.

584
00:43:58,560 --> 00:43:59,560
Come!

585
00:44:00,240 --> 00:44:01,240
Hey.
Give me a hand.

586
00:44:03,600 --> 00:44:04,600
Ugh!

587
00:44:05,120 --> 00:44:06,120
Thanks.

588
00:44:06,400 --> 00:44:07,400
What's up?

589
00:44:10,160 --> 00:44:11,000
What's with the look?

590
00:44:11,040 --> 00:44:12,040
Why would I avoid you?

591
00:44:12,440 --> 00:44:13,440
My precious.

592
00:44:15,520 --> 00:44:17,880
Why would I avoid you? I’m
just cleaning up, can’t you see?

593
00:44:20,000 --> 00:44:21,000
Well..

594
00:44:21,760 --> 00:44:24,080
They say some people from
work are coming over tonight.

595
00:44:24,440 --> 00:44:26,040
So I’m just preparing and stuff, got it?

596
00:44:28,640 --> 00:44:29,640
No.

597
00:44:30,000 --> 00:44:31,320
You're avoiding me.

598
00:44:35,080 --> 00:44:36,440
You gave up on marriage, right?

599
00:44:36,960 --> 00:44:37,960
Do you regret it?

600
00:44:38,000 --> 00:44:39,800
Gorgeous, why would I regret?

601
00:44:40,120 --> 00:44:41,120
What I want..

602
00:44:41,600 --> 00:44:42,800
Is everything to be nice..

603
00:44:43,480 --> 00:44:44,480
And go in order.

604
00:44:45,640 --> 00:44:46,640
In order?
Yes.

605
00:44:47,400 --> 00:44:49,360
Do you think we are in order, Berat?

606
00:44:49,560 --> 00:44:50,840
You didn’t get me a ring

607
00:44:51,120 --> 00:44:52,560
or even tell your mom about me.

608
00:44:52,920 --> 00:44:54,360
And now you're avoiding me.

609
00:44:55,040 --> 00:44:56,519
You went into the channel, Berat

610
00:44:56,520 --> 00:44:57,960
do you think I’m stupid?

611
00:44:58,680 --> 00:44:59,840
I wasn't avoiding, no!

612
00:45:00,000 --> 00:45:00,560
I didn't..

613
00:45:00,880 --> 00:45:01,880
This board..

614
00:45:02,440 --> 00:45:03,520
Was a little loose.

615
00:45:03,920 --> 00:45:04,640
I fixed it.

616
00:45:04,720 --> 00:45:05,720
That’s why I went in.

617
00:45:05,960 --> 00:45:06,960
So..

618
00:45:07,800 --> 00:45:09,160
Gorgeous, don't worry.

619
00:45:09,640 --> 00:45:12,080
I’ll talk to my mother when the time comes.

620
00:45:13,160 --> 00:45:14,160
I'll say that..

621
00:45:14,800 --> 00:45:16,240
I want to marry you.

622
00:45:18,200 --> 00:45:19,320
What about the ring?

623
00:45:25,360 --> 00:45:26,400
Is it a surprise?

624
00:45:28,640 --> 00:45:29,640
Sure, I..

625
00:45:30,240 --> 00:45:32,000
Have some surprises about the ring.

626
00:45:32,200 --> 00:45:32,720
I'm full of..

627
00:45:32,960 --> 00:45:34,040
Surprises, you know.

628
00:45:35,560 --> 00:45:36,840
Alright, nevermind the surprise.

629
00:45:36,880 --> 00:45:38,320
Tell me, how is it like?

630
00:45:38,800 --> 00:45:39,800
No, I can't tell.
Come on!

631
00:45:40,560 --> 00:45:42,000
No, Ela. I can't.

632
00:45:42,280 --> 00:45:43,840
It ruins the surprise, you know?

633
00:45:43,920 --> 00:45:44,920
Oh..

634
00:45:45,080 --> 00:45:46,080
Alright.

635
00:45:46,520 --> 00:45:47,520
Surprise..
I'm so..

636
00:45:47,840 --> 00:45:48,840
I'm so excited.

637
00:45:49,240 --> 00:45:50,480
Okay then, I'll be going.

638
00:45:50,680 --> 00:45:51,680
Okay.

639
00:45:53,040 --> 00:45:54,040
Ela!
Okay.

640
00:45:54,160 --> 00:45:55,160
Be careful!

641
00:45:55,200 --> 00:45:56,320
Alright, I'm so excited.

642
00:45:56,480 --> 00:45:57,000
Surprise.

643
00:45:57,240 --> 00:45:58,240
Yeah, surprise.

644
00:45:59,120 --> 00:46:00,720
Okay, then. I'll see you.

645
00:46:07,520 --> 00:46:09,400
The biggest surprise is for mom.

646
00:46:28,440 --> 00:46:29,760
What do you want this time?

647
00:46:42,080 --> 00:46:42,580
You..

648
00:46:42,840 --> 00:46:44,160
What did you do?

649
00:46:45,320 --> 00:46:47,160
I'll send them where they belong.

650
00:46:47,720 --> 00:46:48,720
Trash!

651
00:46:50,000 --> 00:46:51,200
How would you do that?

652
00:46:52,800 --> 00:46:55,760
Who do you think you are,
questioning me like that?

653
00:46:57,600 --> 00:46:58,600
Let go off me!

654
00:46:58,760 --> 00:46:59,760
Shut your mouth!

655
00:47:00,880 --> 00:47:01,880
Let me go!

656
00:47:03,320 --> 00:47:04,600
What do you want from me?

657
00:47:04,680 --> 00:47:06,016
Why do you keep treating me like this?

658
00:47:06,040 --> 00:47:07,400
What did I do to deserve it?

659
00:47:08,240 --> 00:47:09,240
Look at me..

660
00:47:09,400 --> 00:47:12,320
Who do you think you
are, the lady of the house?

661
00:47:13,040 --> 00:47:15,520
You can’t invite guests without asking me.

662
00:47:16,800 --> 00:47:17,680
I invited Ateş.

663
00:47:17,720 --> 00:47:19,240
You’re unbelievably shameless

664
00:47:19,320 --> 00:47:20,840
and have no pride.

665
00:47:22,680 --> 00:47:24,600
You’re stupid enough

666
00:47:24,840 --> 00:47:28,000
to try making some cheap,
half-assed food just to seduce Ateş.

667
00:47:31,880 --> 00:47:33,520
You think you can make it?

668
00:47:37,360 --> 00:47:39,440
As long as I’m here, neither you

669
00:47:39,480 --> 00:47:40,040
nor your mother

670
00:47:40,280 --> 00:47:43,080
will be walking around this
mansion acting like you own the place.

671
00:47:44,040 --> 00:47:45,960
Your reign is over.

672
00:47:46,400 --> 00:47:49,120
You’re people we paid for and bought.

673
00:47:50,240 --> 00:47:52,840
You got carried away
with this marriage play.

674
00:47:54,120 --> 00:47:54,620
And..

675
00:47:55,000 --> 00:47:55,680
If you think

676
00:47:55,880 --> 00:47:57,280
you can ride on easy money,

677
00:47:57,840 --> 00:47:59,280
you’re out of luck.

678
00:48:00,600 --> 00:48:02,120
You can't talk to me like this.

679
00:48:02,560 --> 00:48:03,680
Well, I did.

680
00:48:04,160 --> 00:48:06,400
You think you’ll try to seduce Ateş

681
00:48:06,840 --> 00:48:08,560
and I’ll just keep quiet, is that it?

682
00:48:10,800 --> 00:48:12,000
Do you trust this?

683
00:48:22,280 --> 00:48:25,560
Did you think a photo together
meant he’d take your side?

684
00:48:35,720 --> 00:48:37,560
You thought he’d stand behind you?

685
00:48:51,600 --> 00:48:53,120
That’s all you’re worth.

686
00:48:55,200 --> 00:48:58,480
I’m sick of you walking around
acting like the lady of the mansion.

687
00:49:22,640 --> 00:49:23,640
Enough!

688
00:49:25,240 --> 00:49:26,240
Stop it.

689
00:49:27,200 --> 00:49:29,320
I told you to stay away from Mercan.

690
00:49:30,760 --> 00:49:32,840
Leave before I break your heart!

691
00:50:22,320 --> 00:50:23,320
Don't cry.

692
00:50:26,240 --> 00:50:27,360
I don't.

693
00:50:31,880 --> 00:50:33,200
Don't mind them.

694
00:50:34,120 --> 00:50:35,280
We can buy the new ones.

695
00:50:36,400 --> 00:50:37,640
It's just clothes.

696
00:50:39,480 --> 00:50:40,760
I don't mind them.

697
00:50:42,520 --> 00:50:44,080
I was going to change.

698
00:50:44,880 --> 00:50:47,760
It was a bit stained, but
it’ll probably come off.

699
00:50:51,160 --> 00:50:53,000
I’m going out for a bit
and I’ll be back soon.

700
00:50:53,200 --> 00:50:54,200
Wait for me in the room.

701
00:50:54,920 --> 00:50:56,480
I'll be back before the guests arrive.

702
00:51:00,320 --> 00:51:01,320
Where?

703
00:51:02,240 --> 00:51:03,240
I'll be back soon.

704
00:51:23,960 --> 00:51:26,360
I've got the chance to
talk to Mr. Kemal but,

705
00:51:26,400 --> 00:51:28,200
I couldn't really learn much.

706
00:51:30,520 --> 00:51:31,520
Boy,

707
00:51:31,880 --> 00:51:34,440
Is that really how you expect
to get anything out of him?

708
00:51:35,480 --> 00:51:36,480
It's okay.

709
00:51:37,840 --> 00:51:38,400
But you..

710
00:51:38,720 --> 00:51:39,880
Keep doing thing anyway.

711
00:51:41,280 --> 00:51:42,760
Observe, trace.

712
00:51:43,560 --> 00:51:44,120
I don't know.

713
00:51:44,320 --> 00:51:47,280
If they head to the study in
the garden, eavesdrop at the door.

714
00:51:48,600 --> 00:51:51,000
I mean this man goes out
to garden at night, right?

715
00:51:52,320 --> 00:51:53,320
Yeah.

716
00:51:53,520 --> 00:51:54,120
Okay, then.

717
00:51:54,520 --> 00:51:55,760
Move in quietly

718
00:51:56,040 --> 00:51:57,720
and eavesdrop on any phone calls.

719
00:52:01,160 --> 00:52:02,560
Okay, Mr. Haydar.

720
00:52:02,600 --> 00:52:03,600
Don't worry.

721
00:52:06,080 --> 00:52:07,960
He's gone through lately.

722
00:52:08,720 --> 00:52:09,720
But it's okay now.

723
00:52:10,520 --> 00:52:12,160
If you help me..

724
00:52:12,480 --> 00:52:14,080
You'll get no problems.

725
00:52:24,400 --> 00:52:26,280
I’ll make you everything in this mansion.

726
00:52:30,840 --> 00:52:31,840
Boy,

727
00:52:31,960 --> 00:52:34,000
of course I'll help you.

728
00:52:35,040 --> 00:52:36,160
I raised you.

729
00:52:40,640 --> 00:52:42,640
What is this man plotting again?

730
00:52:44,320 --> 00:52:45,400
I'll make you marry.

731
00:52:46,360 --> 00:52:47,560
I'll make you have things.

732
00:52:50,320 --> 00:52:51,400
God bless you, Mr. Haydar.

733
00:52:51,480 --> 00:52:52,480
Thanks a lot.

734
00:53:16,520 --> 00:53:18,959
To be honest, I’m glad we didn’t go home.

735
00:53:18,960 --> 00:53:21,240
Otherwise, I’d have been so
tired I would’ve passed out.

736
00:53:21,280 --> 00:53:23,040
I would’ve missed the amazing feast.

737
00:53:25,880 --> 00:53:27,640
So you're sure that you're okay?

738
00:53:30,960 --> 00:53:31,460
Well..

739
00:53:31,600 --> 00:53:32,600
Yes, I am.

740
00:53:32,880 --> 00:53:34,120
Of course you wouldn’t know,

741
00:53:34,160 --> 00:53:36,640
Ever since Mr. Ateş came here,
even the food has improved,

742
00:53:36,680 --> 00:53:37,960
we’re eating first-class now.

743
00:53:38,200 --> 00:53:41,400
I’m not even thinking about what
he’s going to have at his barbecue party.

744
00:53:41,440 --> 00:53:42,440
Yeah?

745
00:53:46,080 --> 00:53:47,080
Demet.

746
00:53:50,240 --> 00:53:52,680
Shall we go to a concert
that you'll choose?

747
00:53:53,800 --> 00:53:54,800
Sure.

748
00:53:57,880 --> 00:53:58,880
Yeah?

749
00:53:59,720 --> 00:54:00,720
Yeah.

750
00:54:01,760 --> 00:54:02,760
What is this?

751
00:54:04,360 --> 00:54:05,400
Are you going somewhere?

752
00:54:07,080 --> 00:54:07,760
Yeah.

753
00:54:08,080 --> 00:54:10,320
Mercan and Ateş are
having a barbecue party.

754
00:54:13,240 --> 00:54:14,240
We'll go there.

755
00:54:15,400 --> 00:54:16,680
Ateş and Mercan..

756
00:54:18,600 --> 00:54:19,600
Okay.

757
00:54:19,800 --> 00:54:20,959
So that there's a party,

758
00:54:20,960 --> 00:54:21,960
I'll take you there.

759
00:54:22,200 --> 00:54:23,640
What are you going to do there?

760
00:54:23,720 --> 00:54:25,920
We'll be there as the
employees of the company.

761
00:54:26,080 --> 00:54:26,760
Demet,

762
00:54:26,840 --> 00:54:28,480
I’m also a partner in this company.

763
00:54:28,600 --> 00:54:29,600
Go.

764
00:54:34,080 --> 00:54:35,320
Mr. Nezih, as usual.

765
00:54:46,320 --> 00:54:48,000
Now, what to do with him?

766
00:54:48,680 --> 00:54:50,400
I'm gonna hit him once..

767
00:54:50,600 --> 00:54:52,679
Dude, nevermind him.

768
00:54:52,680 --> 00:54:56,680
You'll gwt trouble for no reason at all.

769
00:54:56,720 --> 00:54:57,640
Nevermid him.

770
00:54:57,641 --> 00:54:59,120
Let's go eat meatballs.

771
00:54:59,360 --> 00:55:00,840
I'm going to kill him.

772
00:55:00,960 --> 00:55:01,960
For real.
I'm mad.

773
00:55:02,360 --> 00:55:02,880
Nevermind.

774
00:55:02,881 --> 00:55:04,399
Let's go, friends.

775
00:55:04,400 --> 00:55:05,760
Aren't you hungry? Come on.

776
00:55:05,960 --> 00:55:07,880
Come on, you’ll eat the ribs, okay?

777
00:55:12,840 --> 00:55:15,440
Tch, tch. Dust on everything.

778
00:55:16,280 --> 00:55:17,760
Oh God.

779
00:55:56,040 --> 00:55:57,200
Look at this place.

780
00:55:57,400 --> 00:55:58,600
Dust on everything.

781
00:55:59,040 --> 00:56:02,800
We’ve been so caught up with the mansion stuff
that we couldn’t even look after our own place.

782
00:56:22,560 --> 00:56:23,600
What is this here?

783
00:56:25,920 --> 00:56:27,040
Who put this here?

784
00:56:28,720 --> 00:56:29,720
What is this envelope?

785
00:56:31,640 --> 00:56:32,680
Should I open it?

786
00:56:33,240 --> 00:56:33,880
Otherwise..

787
00:56:33,960 --> 00:56:35,840
How would I know who this is for?

788
00:56:36,880 --> 00:56:38,200
I should open it.

789
00:56:54,680 --> 00:56:55,680
What?

790
00:56:56,600 --> 00:56:57,600
Haydar..

791
00:56:57,760 --> 00:56:58,760
Haydar Yıld..

792
00:56:59,000 --> 00:57:00,240
Berat Güneş..

793
00:57:01,400 --> 00:57:02,400
One million?

794
00:57:04,680 --> 00:57:05,680
Oh my God!

795
00:57:05,920 --> 00:57:06,420
Oh!

796
00:57:06,600 --> 00:57:08,400
Did Mr. Haydar give money to Berat?

797
00:57:17,160 --> 00:57:18,720
Oh dear God!

798
00:57:19,760 --> 00:57:21,280
Oh my dear God!

799
00:57:23,560 --> 00:57:24,800
What will I do?

800
00:57:26,680 --> 00:57:27,760
Haydar Yıldırım.

801
00:57:28,280 --> 00:57:29,360
Berat Güneş.

802
00:57:30,120 --> 00:57:31,120
Check.

803
00:57:31,400 --> 00:57:32,400
One million.

804
00:57:33,200 --> 00:57:34,200
Oh God.

805
00:57:34,720 --> 00:57:36,400
Oh God, what do I do?

806
00:57:37,040 --> 00:57:38,520
Oh God, no.

807
00:57:39,160 --> 00:57:40,160
No!

808
00:58:04,120 --> 00:58:05,680
Come on, where are you?

809
00:58:07,400 --> 00:58:08,560
He's about to come, I assume.

810
00:58:11,600 --> 00:58:12,760
Should I call him?

811
00:58:14,240 --> 00:58:14,740
No.

812
00:58:15,080 --> 00:58:15,760
I won't!

813
00:58:16,080 --> 00:58:17,440
He might misunderstand.

814
00:58:17,720 --> 00:58:19,000
Like I'm worried.

815
00:58:21,400 --> 00:58:22,640
But I am.

816
00:58:24,440 --> 00:58:25,440
I will call.

817
00:58:25,680 --> 00:58:26,880
I don't care what he'll think.

818
00:58:37,800 --> 00:58:38,800
Hello?

819
00:58:40,000 --> 00:58:41,000
Where are you?

820
00:58:41,280 --> 00:58:42,400
I'm still waiting for you.

821
00:58:43,800 --> 00:58:44,440
I'm on my way.

822
00:58:44,720 --> 00:58:45,720
I'll be there soon.

823
00:58:47,120 --> 00:58:48,520
I worried when you got late.

824
00:58:50,720 --> 00:58:51,760
How worried?

825
00:58:55,920 --> 00:58:57,440
I knew you would make fun of me.

826
00:58:58,320 --> 00:59:00,240
I was just telling you sincerely.

827
00:59:00,880 --> 00:59:01,640
I'm hanging up.

828
00:59:01,840 --> 00:59:02,840
No, stop.

829
00:59:04,600 --> 00:59:05,600
What's up?

830
00:59:05,640 --> 00:59:07,920
You know, I had something
to tell you yesterday.

831
00:59:10,840 --> 00:59:11,840
Yeah?

832
00:59:12,320 --> 00:59:13,920
I couldn't tell you last night.

833
00:59:14,000 --> 00:59:15,000
We couldn't talk.

834
00:59:18,960 --> 00:59:19,960
Yeah?

835
00:59:21,200 --> 00:59:22,800
It's time to talk.

836
00:59:25,320 --> 00:59:26,440
Talk about what?

837
00:59:28,080 --> 00:59:29,080
When I come.

838
00:59:35,760 --> 00:59:36,760
Ateş?

839
00:59:40,440 --> 00:59:41,440
Ateş?

840
00:59:44,000 --> 00:59:45,000
Ateş!

841
00:59:45,920 --> 00:59:46,920
Oh God!

842
00:59:59,960 --> 01:00:02,360
The person you are trying to
reach is currently unavailable.

843
01:00:33,840 --> 01:00:34,880
Come on already.

844
01:00:50,160 --> 01:00:51,200
Thank God, finally.

845
01:01:05,400 --> 01:01:06,600
Ateş.

846
01:01:13,880 --> 01:01:16,320
Why was I so scared of losing you?

847
01:01:16,720 --> 01:01:18,600
Feels like it took years off my life.

848
01:01:19,200 --> 01:01:20,480
What's happening to me?

849
01:01:20,920 --> 01:01:22,920
Why am I this afraid?

850
01:01:25,160 --> 01:01:28,440
Did the fear of losing me
really upset you that much?

851
01:01:29,080 --> 01:01:31,280
Are those tears really for me?

852
01:01:48,840 --> 01:01:51,720
Thank God. You’re here.

853
01:01:53,320 --> 01:01:57,120
I told you I was fine. Don’t
worry. See? I’m right here.

854
01:01:58,800 --> 01:02:00,440
I thought you were brushing me off.

855
01:02:01,040 --> 01:02:03,080
First the hospital, then the police…

856
01:02:03,720 --> 01:02:05,640
I just panicked.

857
01:02:14,480 --> 01:02:16,520
Cemal wouldn’t take me with him either.

858
01:02:17,600 --> 01:02:19,000
And when I couldn’t see you,

859
01:02:19,080 --> 01:02:21,160
I thought you were all
hiding something from me.

860
01:02:21,360 --> 01:02:22,960
You’re okay, right? Nothing happened?

861
01:02:23,960 --> 01:02:26,000
I’m fine. Don't worry about me.

862
01:02:34,800 --> 01:02:36,000
Why are you crying?

863
01:02:38,040 --> 01:02:40,120
I can't help. My nerves are shot.

864
01:02:40,200 --> 01:02:43,480
That screeching brake
sound… it’s still in my ears.

865
01:02:44,200 --> 01:02:46,080
When the crash happened
right in front of me,

866
01:02:46,160 --> 01:02:47,280
I had to slam the brakes.

867
01:02:47,360 --> 01:02:48,640
There were injured people.

868
01:02:49,000 --> 01:02:51,000
I couldn’t answer the
phone while helping them.

869
01:02:51,400 --> 01:02:52,760
Then my battery died.

870
01:02:52,840 --> 01:02:54,680
After that, everything turned into chaos.

871
01:02:55,160 --> 01:02:57,240
-Everyone’s okay, right? -They’re fine.

872
01:02:57,600 --> 01:02:59,320
We got them to the hospital in time.

873
01:02:59,400 --> 01:03:00,960
Thank God no one was seriously hurt.

874
01:03:03,440 --> 01:03:05,120
You must be exhausted.

875
01:03:05,200 --> 01:03:07,720
We can call them and cancel if
you want. They’ll understand.

876
01:03:07,800 --> 01:03:09,480
I’m not tired.

877
01:03:10,200 --> 01:03:12,480
And they’re probably on
their way. It’d be rude.

878
01:03:12,720 --> 01:03:14,360
Let’s go get changed.

879
01:03:15,000 --> 01:03:17,560
Cemal told me not to say
anything to your family.

880
01:03:19,040 --> 01:03:20,920
That's right. I asked him to.

881
01:03:21,560 --> 01:03:23,200
No need to worry them.

882
01:03:23,680 --> 01:03:26,600
I still don’t understand
why you left so suddenly.

883
01:03:28,200 --> 01:03:30,640
You’ll understand soon. Come on.

884
01:03:45,040 --> 01:03:47,400
Oh, Berat… Oh, Berat…

885
01:03:47,720 --> 01:03:50,600
just wait till I get my hands
on you. You’ll see what I’ll do.

886
01:03:51,080 --> 01:03:52,600
Ah... he's coming.

887
01:03:53,880 --> 01:03:55,560
Where have you been?

888
01:03:56,800 --> 01:04:00,760
Mom, I had things to take
care of. I handled them.

889
01:04:01,680 --> 01:04:04,320
What is this?! Tell me.

890
01:04:10,840 --> 01:04:13,720
Tell me what kind of dirty
business did you get into with Haydar.

891
01:04:16,000 --> 01:04:19,280
What dirty business?! Mom, no!

892
01:04:19,680 --> 01:04:20,760
It’s nothing like that!

893
01:04:20,920 --> 01:04:23,400
Then what is it? Tell me!

894
01:04:26,880 --> 01:04:30,440
I took it to pay our debt to Malik.

895
01:04:31,880 --> 01:04:34,720
Obviously, Mr. Haydar didn’t
give you this out of kindness.

896
01:04:35,840 --> 01:04:39,400
Well, mom, he didn’t ask for anything bad.

897
01:04:40,920 --> 01:04:42,800
He just said, "Be friends with Mr. Cemal.

898
01:04:43,040 --> 01:04:46,640
Find out who he is, what he’s about."

899
01:04:48,120 --> 01:04:50,240
What’s Mr. Haydar's
problem with Cemal, anyway?

900
01:04:51,160 --> 01:04:52,680
He didn’t say, mom.

901
01:04:54,800 --> 01:04:56,960
There’s definitely
something shady going on here.

902
01:04:57,040 --> 01:04:59,320
If his intentions were
good, he would’ve told you.

903
01:04:59,400 --> 01:05:01,880
Listen to me, Berat.
Stay away from that man.

904
01:05:02,200 --> 01:05:05,160
If you get mixed up in
Haydar’s shady business,

905
01:05:05,240 --> 01:05:07,720
I won’t forgive you.
Not as your mother. Got it?

906
01:05:08,920 --> 01:05:10,320
Alright, mom.

907
01:05:10,400 --> 01:05:13,040
-Did you understand?! -I did. Okay. I did.

908
01:05:14,560 --> 01:05:16,400
Why are you getting so worked up?

909
01:05:22,680 --> 01:05:24,800
Oh God.

910
01:05:29,960 --> 01:05:32,120
Mom, you obviously know something…

911
01:05:33,320 --> 01:05:35,800
There’s definitely
something you’re not saying.

912
01:05:36,880 --> 01:05:38,840
Ugh… we'll see what it is.

913
01:05:53,240 --> 01:05:54,480
What’s all this?

914
01:05:56,960 --> 01:05:58,440
Did you… buy these?

915
01:05:59,840 --> 01:06:01,960
You can’t live your whole
life in the same dress.

916
01:06:02,360 --> 01:06:06,640
Is that why you left?

917
01:06:22,400 --> 01:06:23,880
Ateş?

918
01:06:24,280 --> 01:06:26,120
Mercan?

919
01:06:29,160 --> 01:06:30,720
You’re teasing me again.

920
01:06:32,080 --> 01:06:33,880
But you’re actually not.

921
01:06:34,560 --> 01:06:35,920
I’ve figured you out now.

922
01:06:40,760 --> 01:06:43,600
But you didn’t have to.
I could’ve handled it.

923
01:06:45,000 --> 01:06:46,640
I had to.

924
01:06:48,640 --> 01:06:50,480
I won’t ignore the injustice done to you.

925
01:06:52,080 --> 01:06:53,800
Please don’t argue.

926
01:06:57,560 --> 01:07:00,480
Okay. I’m not.

927
01:07:04,440 --> 01:07:06,480
You have your own sense of justice.

928
01:07:07,200 --> 01:07:08,680
You never waver.

929
01:07:08,880 --> 01:07:10,960
You always make things right immediately.

930
01:07:11,760 --> 01:07:13,680
You never let anything stay broken.

931
01:07:14,120 --> 01:07:16,400
You never let anything
fall apart and stay that way.

932
01:07:17,520 --> 01:07:21,160
Knowing that… it gives
a person a little comfort.

933
01:07:23,640 --> 01:07:24,920
Thank you.

934
01:07:27,480 --> 01:07:28,560
You’re welcome.

935
01:07:33,520 --> 01:07:35,840
And thank you… for the kind words.

936
01:07:37,360 --> 01:07:39,680
Let’s see if we can get
through today without a fight.

937
01:07:40,560 --> 01:07:41,560
Why would you say that?

938
01:07:42,280 --> 01:07:47,240
Every time we make peace, a fight
follows. Something always breaks.

939
01:07:50,360 --> 01:07:51,920
Let’s not let it happen this time.

940
01:07:53,680 --> 01:07:54,880
Okay.

941
01:07:58,080 --> 01:07:59,320
I hope you like them.

942
01:08:00,640 --> 01:08:02,000
I already do.

943
01:08:02,160 --> 01:08:04,080
I loved them all before even seeing them.

944
01:08:05,400 --> 01:08:07,480
I’ll remember today forever.

945
01:08:09,080 --> 01:08:11,920
I hope it fits. Check it.
If not, you can exchange it.

946
01:08:12,640 --> 01:08:14,240
You’re tiny anyway.

947
01:08:15,200 --> 01:08:16,520
Me?

948
01:08:18,880 --> 01:08:21,320
I’m not exchanging anything.
I know I’ll love them.

949
01:08:23,000 --> 01:08:25,520
Then, I’ll try one on right away.

950
01:08:27,480 --> 01:08:29,040
And I’ll change right here.

951
01:08:41,160 --> 01:08:42,840
Where is that witch Nermin?!

952
01:08:43,320 --> 01:08:45,400
She’s going to pay for getting in my way!

953
01:08:46,120 --> 01:08:47,640
Mom, calm down.

954
01:08:47,720 --> 01:08:50,040
You’re only giving her what she wants.

955
01:08:50,760 --> 01:08:53,760
I don’t care, Aslı. Just let her come...

956
01:08:54,320 --> 01:08:56,600
Were you looking for me, Mrs. Müzeyyen?

957
01:08:56,920 --> 01:08:58,720
Yes! I was!

958
01:08:59,720 --> 01:09:00,880
Well, here I am.

959
01:09:05,280 --> 01:09:09,360
Oh, sweetheart… you look upset.

960
01:09:11,560 --> 01:09:13,040
But I understand you.

961
01:09:13,920 --> 01:09:17,080
Competing with Nermin Yıldırım isn’t easy.

962
01:09:21,360 --> 01:09:23,320
But don’t dwell on it.

963
01:09:24,480 --> 01:09:27,000
It doesn’t matter who the president is.

964
01:09:27,680 --> 01:09:29,640
What matters is the
future of the foundation.

965
01:09:35,560 --> 01:09:40,400
You’ll see, as the new
president, I’ll take it to the top.

966
01:09:44,600 --> 01:09:47,200
Becoming president with the
necklace you stole from me…

967
01:09:47,560 --> 01:09:50,000
suits someone like you.

968
01:09:52,080 --> 01:09:54,720
And forget taking it to the top

969
01:09:55,440 --> 01:09:57,840
you’ll drag the foundation
straight to the bottom.

970
01:10:01,760 --> 01:10:03,520
I’m sure of it.

971
01:10:25,440 --> 01:10:26,680
Are you ready?

972
01:10:27,280 --> 01:10:28,680
I'm coming!

973
01:11:06,920 --> 01:11:09,560
You drive me crazy every single time.

974
01:11:17,120 --> 01:11:18,560
I love this one.

975
01:11:19,360 --> 01:11:21,480
You? How does it look? Does it suit me?

976
01:11:35,040 --> 01:11:36,320
It…

977
01:11:38,680 --> 01:11:39,920
It suits you beautifully.

978
01:11:50,440 --> 01:11:52,120
It fits perfectly.

979
01:11:53,080 --> 01:11:55,080
I didn’t know you knew me this well.

980
01:11:56,480 --> 01:11:59,320
There was someone your size
there. I just described you.

981
01:12:02,200 --> 01:12:03,240
Like what?

982
01:12:03,960 --> 01:12:06,000
You liked it on someone else?

983
01:12:07,120 --> 01:12:08,760
You'd better buy it for her, then.

984
01:12:28,640 --> 01:12:30,600
Believe me, it didn’t
look half as good on her.

985
01:12:49,440 --> 01:12:51,120
It’s not just the dress.

986
01:12:53,560 --> 01:12:54,880
It’s who’s wearing it.

987
01:13:00,600 --> 01:13:05,920
My God, what is he telling me?

988
01:13:22,680 --> 01:13:24,200
Thank you.

989
01:13:27,880 --> 01:13:29,360
Just in time.

990
01:13:36,520 --> 01:13:37,840
Let me…

991
01:13:39,120 --> 01:13:40,400
What’s wrong with it?

992
01:13:41,320 --> 01:13:44,640
It’s a little messy. I’ll take care of it.

993
01:14:15,320 --> 01:14:16,720
There. Better…

994
01:14:22,960 --> 01:14:24,560
Why were you so scared?

995
01:14:28,760 --> 01:14:31,960
I was just… scared. Isn’t that normal?

996
01:14:34,320 --> 01:14:36,360
Scared of losing me?

997
01:14:45,440 --> 01:14:49,640
I thought something happened. That’s all.

998
01:14:53,160 --> 01:14:56,120
And then you… went out just to get a dress…

999
01:15:00,720 --> 01:15:01,800
I should go downstairs.

1000
01:15:01,880 --> 01:15:04,400
They must have already arrived.
No need to make them wait.

1001
01:15:39,360 --> 01:15:41,720
Haven’t you calmed down yet, Mom?

1002
01:15:42,960 --> 01:15:44,720
How can I calm down, dear?

1003
01:15:45,760 --> 01:15:47,440
That witch drove me mad.

1004
01:15:48,120 --> 01:15:50,960
Nermin, Haydar, their daughters…
I’ve had enough of all of them!

1005
01:15:53,880 --> 01:15:56,000
If I knew Ateş wouldn’t stop me,

1006
01:15:56,080 --> 01:15:58,080
I’d kill every one of them one by one.

1007
01:15:59,000 --> 01:16:00,240
I keep telling you.

1008
01:16:00,720 --> 01:16:04,320
Nermin and Haydar are easy targets…

1009
01:16:04,840 --> 01:16:06,360
Our biggest threat is Mercan.

1010
01:16:07,920 --> 01:16:09,560
Maybe it’s time to end this.

1011
01:16:10,920 --> 01:16:12,760
What are you trying to say, dear?!

1012
01:16:17,040 --> 01:16:20,240
If Mercan finds out why
Ateş really came here...

1013
01:16:20,560 --> 01:16:22,440
His revenge plan...

1014
01:16:22,880 --> 01:16:24,280
Are you out of your mind?!

1015
01:16:25,600 --> 01:16:28,400
Never! That will never happen!
Get that out of your head!

1016
01:16:31,280 --> 01:16:33,960
If we do that, we put both
Ateş and ourselves in danger.

1017
01:16:34,680 --> 01:16:36,760
Then give me a better idea, Mom.

1018
01:16:37,600 --> 01:16:39,760
How will you keep Mercan away from Ateş?

1019
01:16:40,600 --> 01:16:42,120
Don’t you see what’s happening?

1020
01:16:42,800 --> 01:16:44,400
And what are we waiting for?

1021
01:16:46,080 --> 01:16:48,800
If I stay silent, I’ll
lose Ateş completely.

1022
01:16:50,920 --> 01:16:53,160
Don’t! I said don’t.

1023
01:16:53,920 --> 01:16:56,880
This conversation is over.
Don’t bring this to me again.

1024
01:17:19,160 --> 01:17:20,680
What are you doing here?

1025
01:17:20,760 --> 01:17:21,920
Were you waiting for me?

1026
01:17:24,080 --> 01:17:26,360
Did you talk to your
mother? What did she say?

1027
01:17:26,680 --> 01:17:28,320
What talk, my sultan?

1028
01:17:28,640 --> 01:17:29,840
What mother?

1029
01:17:30,760 --> 01:17:32,200
I’m waiting for Mr. Haydar.

1030
01:17:33,720 --> 01:17:35,480
So when will you talk to her?

1031
01:17:36,720 --> 01:17:38,040
As soon as possible.

1032
01:17:38,680 --> 01:17:39,680
Maybe today?

1033
01:17:40,400 --> 01:17:42,640
-No, not that soon. -Tomorrow?

1034
01:17:45,120 --> 01:17:47,440
Why are you suffocating
me like this, Zehra?

1035
01:17:47,720 --> 01:17:51,840
Look at me. Are you
stringing me along? Huh?

1036
01:17:53,840 --> 01:17:54,960
No, Zehra.

1037
01:17:55,040 --> 01:17:58,080
No, dear. No, my love.
I’m not stringing you along.

1038
01:17:58,280 --> 01:18:00,040
Enough, Berat! I'm sick of this!

1039
01:18:00,440 --> 01:18:01,480
Look, Berat.

1040
01:18:01,640 --> 01:18:03,480
Either you talk to your mother by tonight,

1041
01:18:03,560 --> 01:18:05,480
or you forget about me! Do you understand?

1042
01:18:06,160 --> 01:18:07,520
That’s my final word!

1043
01:18:23,360 --> 01:18:25,040
Man… unbelievable.

1044
01:18:34,280 --> 01:18:36,280
Yes, Ms. Binnaz? Anything you want to say?

1045
01:18:37,080 --> 01:18:39,200
Yes. Yes, there is.

1046
01:18:39,920 --> 01:18:41,840
I have a few words for you.

1047
01:19:01,560 --> 01:19:05,720
Mr Haydar. Until today, I
treated this mansion as my home

1048
01:19:06,440 --> 01:19:08,320
and you as my family.

1049
01:19:09,160 --> 01:19:12,120
I sheltered here with my children.

1050
01:19:13,200 --> 01:19:17,400
Every sin committed within
these walls is on your shoulders.

1051
01:19:18,160 --> 01:19:21,720
But if you try to drag
my children into those sins

1052
01:19:22,120 --> 01:19:24,280
if you hurt them,

1053
01:19:25,360 --> 01:19:28,760
This silent tongue will
speak, just so you know.

1054
01:19:30,760 --> 01:19:32,520
What are you implying, Binnaz?

1055
01:19:32,600 --> 01:19:34,120
Are you threatening me, openly?

1056
01:19:34,840 --> 01:19:37,000
Instead of thanking
me for helping your son,

1057
01:19:37,080 --> 01:19:39,040
you stand here questioning me?

1058
01:19:39,840 --> 01:19:41,600
Staying silent isn’t an option for you.

1059
01:19:42,280 --> 01:19:44,480
It’s a necessity. Don’t forget that.

1060
01:19:45,960 --> 01:19:50,000
I’m aware of my duty and my obligations.

1061
01:19:50,200 --> 01:19:52,240
And I'm fulfilling them, Mr. Haydar.

1062
01:19:52,920 --> 01:19:54,520
But don’t forget this either...

1063
01:19:54,600 --> 01:19:58,080
A mother will do anything for her children.

1064
01:19:58,160 --> 01:20:00,560
If necessary, I’ll risk everything.

1065
01:20:34,000 --> 01:20:35,960
Welcome. Welcome. Nice to see you.

1066
01:20:36,200 --> 01:20:37,560
Hello, Burak.

1067
01:20:37,720 --> 01:20:40,880
Mr. Ateş. Mrs. Mercan.

1068
01:20:41,880 --> 01:20:42,880
Welcome.

1069
01:20:46,600 --> 01:20:49,360
My brother’s coming too, just so you know.

1070
01:20:49,720 --> 01:20:51,680
I tried so hard but couldn’t shake him off.

1071
01:20:52,320 --> 01:20:54,800
He dropped me off and went
to get your favorite dessert.

1072
01:20:55,040 --> 01:20:56,400
He’ll be here soon.

1073
01:20:57,000 --> 01:20:58,880
He didn’t have to bother…

1074
01:21:03,560 --> 01:21:05,160
Welcome, everyone.

1075
01:21:05,240 --> 01:21:06,280
Oh, Mr. Cemal's here.

1076
01:21:06,360 --> 01:21:07,800
Welcome.

1077
01:21:10,120 --> 01:21:12,600
Mercan, I love your dress.

1078
01:21:12,680 --> 01:21:15,960
The color, the cut... everything.
It looks amazing on you.

1079
01:21:17,000 --> 01:21:18,360
Thank you.

1080
01:21:22,280 --> 01:21:23,640
It is a gift from Ateş.

1081
01:21:25,800 --> 01:21:28,680
I love it too, Mercan.
Your dress is on fire.

1082
01:21:30,680 --> 01:21:33,040
You two look great together
as a couple, Mr. Ateş.

1083
01:21:35,320 --> 01:21:38,480
I was just going to say the same. You
took the words right out of my mouth.

1084
01:21:57,040 --> 01:22:00,400
Come on, move along.
You’re left standing. Go on.

1085
01:22:00,800 --> 01:22:03,760
-Yes, please. Come on, this way. -Please.

1086
01:22:03,840 --> 01:22:05,200
Let's go, dear.

1087
01:22:23,760 --> 01:22:25,280
My God, what is this?

1088
01:22:25,400 --> 01:22:28,960
It was so funny though.

1089
01:22:35,800 --> 01:22:37,480
She was really funny.

1090
01:22:37,680 --> 01:22:39,640
I watched that movie.
It was really awesome.

1091
01:22:39,720 --> 01:22:41,680
I adore that actress, too.

1092
01:22:41,840 --> 01:22:45,600
- The woman was so funny.
- Yes, she really was.

1093
01:22:58,480 --> 01:22:59,960
Excuse me.

1094
01:23:05,480 --> 01:23:06,840
You're not cold, are you?

1095
01:23:07,120 --> 01:23:08,640
No, I'm not. You?

1096
01:23:16,120 --> 01:23:17,880
There's no reason to be cold, anyway.

1097
01:23:18,200 --> 01:23:20,480
I just asked since I
didn’t want you getting sick.

1098
01:23:32,760 --> 01:23:34,600
What’s the point of all this?

1099
01:23:35,800 --> 01:23:38,000
Aslı, our meat and our
grill are right here.

1100
01:23:38,080 --> 01:23:40,760
Everyone’s gathered.
Why don’t you have fun?

1101
01:23:46,880 --> 01:23:48,440
With that girl here?

1102
01:23:49,000 --> 01:23:50,880
Aslı, you’re about to go down in history

1103
01:23:50,960 --> 01:23:53,040
as the first person to
ruin my mood at the grill.

1104
01:23:53,120 --> 01:23:55,360
How many times ave I told
you she’s not at fault.

1105
01:23:59,800 --> 01:24:01,200
Let me check Cemal.

1106
01:24:06,080 --> 01:24:07,160
Everything okay?

1107
01:24:08,120 --> 01:24:09,240
Yeah. Yeah.

1108
01:24:09,320 --> 01:24:10,520
Everything’s perfect.

1109
01:24:17,720 --> 01:24:18,760
Don’t mind her.

1110
01:24:19,400 --> 01:24:20,640
So what about you?

1111
01:24:22,080 --> 01:24:23,720
What are you asking about me?

1112
01:24:23,960 --> 01:24:27,720
I see. You’re going to pretend
again like there’s no fire inside you.

1113
01:24:28,880 --> 01:24:31,960
The other heart has already
caught fire, just so you know.

1114
01:24:33,480 --> 01:24:34,480
Which heart?

1115
01:24:34,560 --> 01:24:37,640
Which heart do you
think? Obviously not mine.

1116
01:25:02,360 --> 01:25:04,400
By the way, can I tell you something?

1117
01:25:06,000 --> 01:25:10,520
Mercan almost lost her mind today.
Worse than the day you were kidnapped.

1118
01:25:11,760 --> 01:25:14,040
- So she was really scared?
- More than you think.

1119
01:25:22,480 --> 01:25:23,960
-I'll be back. -Okay, dear.

1120
01:25:28,200 --> 01:25:29,560
Good luck.

1121
01:25:29,640 --> 01:25:31,920
If it’s easy, come do it yourself.

1122
01:25:32,000 --> 01:25:34,600
No thanks. I’ve cooked enough for today.

1123
01:25:34,680 --> 01:25:36,560
It’s better for all of you if I don’t.

1124
01:25:37,000 --> 01:25:39,600
She thinks you can make
dry dolma without onions.

1125
01:25:40,280 --> 01:25:41,440
That bad?

1126
01:25:42,600 --> 01:25:43,840
Oh, come on.

1127
01:26:02,040 --> 01:26:03,920
Hey everyone. Hello.

1128
01:26:05,680 --> 01:26:07,480
What's Mr. Nezir doing here?

1129
01:26:11,440 --> 01:26:16,560
Hello. Mercan, I got
this especially for you.

1130
01:26:16,680 --> 01:26:18,680
Thanks. You shouldn’t have. Really.

1131
01:26:21,000 --> 01:26:22,360
You really went to the trouble.

1132
01:26:29,520 --> 01:26:30,600
It’s no trouble.

1133
01:26:32,880 --> 01:26:34,560
You know, it’s a pleasure for me.

1134
01:26:41,080 --> 01:26:43,120
So, how are you? Everything okay?

1135
01:26:46,520 --> 01:26:47,720
We’re fine.

1136
01:26:53,400 --> 01:26:54,600
So glad you came.

1137
01:26:56,160 --> 01:26:57,760
Thank you.

1138
01:26:58,520 --> 01:26:59,680
Why don't you come over?

1139
01:27:14,240 --> 01:27:18,320
These meats… I’m about
to give you all a real feast.

1140
01:27:18,480 --> 01:27:20,960
-Thank you. -Don't overcook the meatballs.

1141
01:27:23,720 --> 01:27:25,360
Mercan likes them medium.

1142
01:28:01,240 --> 01:28:02,360
The meatballs are ready.

1143
01:28:02,480 --> 01:28:05,160
Everything’s done. Please,
everyone, come to the table.

1144
01:28:12,280 --> 01:28:13,880
Ugh, I’m starving.

1145
01:28:26,000 --> 01:28:27,240
How are things with Burak?

1146
01:28:27,320 --> 01:28:29,720
Better. I think we’re improving.

1147
01:28:29,920 --> 01:28:32,120
He invited me to a concert this weekend.

1148
01:28:46,960 --> 01:28:48,840
I’m so happy for you.
That’s wonderful news.

1149
01:28:49,480 --> 01:28:50,960
Now you tell me.

1150
01:28:51,400 --> 01:28:53,560
-Me? -Of course you, Mercan.

1151
01:28:53,800 --> 01:28:55,440
Look, your face is glowing.

1152
01:28:55,960 --> 01:28:59,160
And the way you and Ateş look
at each other didn’t escape me.

1153
01:29:08,560 --> 01:29:11,480
Come on, where did you
get that from, Demet?

1154
01:29:12,400 --> 01:29:14,600
There’s no such thing.
You must’ve seen wrong.

1155
01:29:15,080 --> 01:29:17,720
Alright. If you say there’s
nothing, then there’s nothing.

1156
01:29:17,920 --> 01:29:19,800
-Mm-hmm. -Mm‑hmm.

1157
01:29:29,400 --> 01:29:30,840
What am I doing?

1158
01:29:31,720 --> 01:29:33,720
Am I giving people the wrong impression?

1159
01:29:35,280 --> 01:29:36,640
No… I don’t think so.

1160
01:29:37,720 --> 01:29:41,120
We’re just always together,
that’s why they misunderstand.

1161
01:30:23,680 --> 01:30:26,920
While you eat, lend me your
ears for a moment, friends.

1162
01:30:28,560 --> 01:30:30,880
Don’t worry, I’m not
planning a long or boring speech.

1163
01:30:31,920 --> 01:30:35,920
Thank you all for your hard work,
on behalf of myself and Mercan.

1164
01:30:36,440 --> 01:30:38,440
Without your dedication,

1165
01:30:38,840 --> 01:30:41,760
we couldn’t have prepared the
project presentation this quickly.

1166
01:30:43,400 --> 01:30:44,720
The results aren’t in yet,

1167
01:30:45,280 --> 01:30:48,120
but this teamwork deserves a celebration.

1168
01:30:55,960 --> 01:30:57,360
Good for you.

1169
01:31:02,440 --> 01:31:03,560
And a special thanks

1170
01:31:04,920 --> 01:31:08,920
to the brain of the project,
my wife, Mercan Karahan.

1171
01:31:17,160 --> 01:31:22,320
Without her sharp mind, creativity,
passion, and determination,

1172
01:31:22,400 --> 01:31:23,760
this project wouldn’t exist.

1173
01:31:27,560 --> 01:31:28,760
Thank you.

1174
01:31:29,440 --> 01:31:31,920
Those qualities belong
to all of us, not just me.

1175
01:31:37,440 --> 01:31:39,120
Then, enjoy your meal everyone.

1176
01:31:39,360 --> 01:31:40,640
Enjoy.

1177
01:31:41,400 --> 01:31:43,520
Enjoy it. Thank you.

1178
01:31:53,920 --> 01:31:55,040
I’m going to be sick.

1179
01:31:55,720 --> 01:31:58,600
Don’t do it in front of everyone.

1180
01:31:59,760 --> 01:32:01,760
Come on, don’t look
like that. Smile a little.

1181
01:32:02,600 --> 01:32:04,040
This game needs to end.

1182
01:32:10,480 --> 01:32:11,920
I’m tired of it.

1183
01:32:14,440 --> 01:32:15,800
Want some salad?

1184
01:32:17,200 --> 01:32:18,760
Yes, but just a little.

1185
01:32:22,840 --> 01:32:24,360
Thank you.

1186
01:32:28,920 --> 01:32:31,280
Here, Aslı, let me pass that to you.

1187
01:32:31,840 --> 01:32:33,280
Never mind, I don’t want it.

1188
01:32:37,080 --> 01:32:39,320
I have to speak with a client now.

1189
01:32:56,520 --> 01:32:57,600
There.

1190
01:33:01,640 --> 01:33:03,200
Why were you so scared?

1191
01:33:09,400 --> 01:33:11,720
- Would you like some bread?
- No, I don’t eat bread.

1192
01:33:12,080 --> 01:33:13,400
You don't?

1193
01:33:14,240 --> 01:33:16,160
So, we're cautious about our health.

1194
01:33:33,440 --> 01:33:34,640
Where are you going?

1195
01:33:34,880 --> 01:33:36,240
… to the bathroom.

1196
01:33:36,840 --> 01:33:38,200
Of course.

1197
01:33:43,120 --> 01:33:44,520
Everything looks amazing.

1198
01:33:46,880 --> 01:33:48,880
-You liked it? -Very much.

1199
01:33:49,960 --> 01:33:52,400
It wouldn't have turned out
any better without your help.

1200
01:33:54,440 --> 01:33:57,800
If we do something together, there’s
no chance it won’t turn out well.

1201
01:34:14,400 --> 01:34:16,480
How did you know what I needed?

1202
01:34:21,480 --> 01:34:22,960
That’s my secret.

1203
01:34:33,040 --> 01:34:34,280
Come on, all together.

1204
01:34:34,520 --> 01:34:37,640
Your brows are dark enough

1205
01:34:37,760 --> 01:34:41,080
to ink a decree.

1206
01:34:41,200 --> 01:34:44,480
This love drives me

1207
01:34:44,560 --> 01:34:47,400
from one land to another.

1208
01:34:48,040 --> 01:34:51,560
Even if Lokman the Healer came,

1209
01:34:51,640 --> 01:34:55,040
he’d only deepen my wound.

1210
01:34:55,360 --> 01:34:58,640
Let my beloved come

1211
01:34:58,720 --> 01:35:01,000
and tend to it herself.

1212
01:35:01,080 --> 01:35:02,200
Bravo!

1213
01:35:02,280 --> 01:35:04,280
You sang perfectly. Thank you all.

1214
01:35:11,520 --> 01:35:14,760
Well done, Mr. Cemal. You were really good.

1215
01:35:14,840 --> 01:35:17,520
-You sang so well, Mr. Cemal. -Thanks.

1216
01:35:18,920 --> 01:35:21,200
-Well done, Cemal. -Thank you.

1217
01:35:21,440 --> 01:35:25,440
Mr. Ateş, this gathering was
such a good idea. Thank you so much.

1218
01:35:25,800 --> 01:35:29,960
Absolutely. I don’t know about you all,
but I had so much fun. I enjoyed it a lot.

1219
01:36:02,280 --> 01:36:03,560
Ugh.

1220
01:36:04,560 --> 01:36:06,200
What are you doing here?

1221
01:36:06,680 --> 01:36:09,400
I… I just came out of the bathroom.

1222
01:36:09,880 --> 01:36:11,200
Then I couldn’t find the door.

1223
01:36:11,960 --> 01:36:13,480
Oh, is that so?

1224
01:36:16,920 --> 01:36:20,320
You’ll leave through
the same door you came in.

1225
01:36:21,560 --> 01:36:26,040
The-the house is so
big… I couldn’t remember.

1226
01:36:28,640 --> 01:36:30,320
I'll go now.

1227
01:37:01,440 --> 01:37:03,240
This is a photo of Haydar from his youth.

1228
01:37:05,080 --> 01:37:06,960
What is it doing in this guy’s wallet?

1229
01:37:15,200 --> 01:37:17,960
"To my Nurgül." I don’t believe this.

1230
01:37:19,720 --> 01:37:20,960
No, no…

1231
01:37:26,000 --> 01:37:27,280
What does this mean?

1232
01:37:28,360 --> 01:37:29,560
Could it be…?

1233
01:37:51,880 --> 01:37:53,400
Malik.

1234
01:37:53,560 --> 01:37:56,000
There’s so much work today.
My mom will be here soon.

1235
01:37:56,120 --> 01:37:58,960
-Why did you come, my love? MALİK:
-I wanted to talk to you, Çiçek.

1236
01:38:00,960 --> 01:38:02,280
What's wrong?

1237
01:38:04,360 --> 01:38:08,200
Everything we’ve been through,
all the trouble… it’s because of me.

1238
01:38:09,280 --> 01:38:11,240
I know you’ve been hurting.

1239
01:38:11,720 --> 01:38:13,200
And I can’t stand it.

1240
01:38:14,440 --> 01:38:17,600
Why are you talking like this,
Malik? None of this is your fault.

1241
01:38:18,640 --> 01:38:20,640
Mrs. Binnaz is right, Çiçek.

1242
01:38:23,560 --> 01:38:24,800
About what?

1243
01:38:28,680 --> 01:38:30,840
Malik! Are you going to
tell me what’s going on?

1244
01:38:42,080 --> 01:38:43,640
Ugh, where’s my wallet?

1245
01:38:58,640 --> 01:39:00,160
Ah, here it is.

1246
01:39:14,040 --> 01:39:15,200
How are you, son?

1247
01:39:15,480 --> 01:39:17,240
I’m fine, thank you, sir. And you?

1248
01:39:18,800 --> 01:39:20,680
It felt strange seeing you here.

1249
01:39:21,240 --> 01:39:23,520
I’m used to seeing you
working at the company.

1250
01:39:26,080 --> 01:39:27,960
I used to work a lot too

1251
01:39:29,000 --> 01:39:30,360
when I was young.

1252
01:39:30,880 --> 01:39:33,120
My circumstances weren’t great back then.

1253
01:39:36,280 --> 01:39:37,920
Hard work is good.

1254
01:39:38,760 --> 01:39:39,960
You’re right, sir.

1255
01:39:42,560 --> 01:39:44,400
I had a son too.

1256
01:39:51,080 --> 01:39:53,520
He wasn’t very good with work.

1257
01:39:54,400 --> 01:39:55,640
Always fooling around.

1258
01:39:56,280 --> 01:39:58,080
We didn’t get along much because of that.

1259
01:40:01,320 --> 01:40:04,200
I grew up without a father.

1260
01:40:05,040 --> 01:40:06,840
So I never had those conflicts.

1261
01:40:11,600 --> 01:40:14,000
Anyway, my friends will
wonder where I am. I should go.

1262
01:40:24,720 --> 01:40:26,080
I really put my foot in it.

1263
01:40:54,560 --> 01:40:56,240
What are you implying, Binnaz?

1264
01:40:56,480 --> 01:40:58,080
Are you threatening me, openly?

1265
01:40:58,680 --> 01:41:00,520
Instead of thanking
me for helping your son,

1266
01:41:00,600 --> 01:41:02,280
you stand here questioning me?

1267
01:41:03,640 --> 01:41:05,360
Staying silent isn’t an option for you.

1268
01:41:06,080 --> 01:41:08,240
It’s a necessity. Don’t forget that.

1269
01:43:24,040 --> 01:43:25,240
Where have you been?

1270
01:43:25,480 --> 01:43:29,160
I think I ate too much.
Took a walk to settle it.

1271
01:43:43,360 --> 01:43:45,720
Coming here was good
for all of us, wasn't it?

1272
01:43:45,840 --> 01:43:47,840
Yes, it really was.

1273
01:43:47,920 --> 01:43:50,480
We must do this more often, Ms. Zahide.

1274
01:43:50,760 --> 01:43:51,760
Um-hmm.

1275
01:43:51,840 --> 01:43:53,080
In the meantime…

1276
01:43:53,600 --> 01:43:56,320
There’s a different energy
between Mr. Ateş and Mrs. Mercan.

1277
01:43:56,400 --> 01:43:58,840
There's a difference in their
style. It looks good though.

1278
01:43:59,080 --> 01:44:01,120
I sure noticed.

1279
01:44:07,040 --> 01:44:08,080
Mr. Ateş?

1280
01:44:10,240 --> 01:44:12,680
I'd like to say
something, if you excuse me.

1281
01:44:13,240 --> 01:44:14,320
Sure. Go ahead.

1282
01:44:14,760 --> 01:44:17,120
Are we going to celebrate like this?

1283
01:44:17,200 --> 01:44:19,280
Let me take care of it, if you’ll allow me.

1284
01:44:22,280 --> 01:44:23,440
Of course.

1285
01:44:24,080 --> 01:44:25,120
Mrs. Mercan?

1286
01:44:25,840 --> 01:44:26,960
Please, go ahead.

1287
01:44:28,040 --> 01:44:32,760
Then this song is from me to you.

1288
01:44:34,520 --> 01:44:37,040
Oh, this is the best
song. Come on. Let's dance.

1289
01:44:37,120 --> 01:44:38,680
Everyone dance. Come on.

1290
01:44:56,640 --> 01:44:59,200
Come on, Ateş. Get up.
We can't do without you.

1291
01:45:00,240 --> 01:45:01,440
Come on.

1292
01:46:38,200 --> 01:46:40,240
Come on, Aslı. No objections. Get up.

1293
01:46:40,320 --> 01:46:43,280
We'll dance together. Don't do
that, at least today. Come on.

1294
01:46:58,920 --> 01:47:01,120
Come on, brother.

1295
01:47:01,480 --> 01:47:02,520
What? Come on. Get up.

1296
01:47:02,600 --> 01:47:04,600
-Don't be ridiculous. -Come on. Get up.

1297
01:47:05,400 --> 01:47:06,480
Come on.

1298
01:47:07,560 --> 01:47:09,800
- Come on.
- What does that have to do with anything?

1299
01:50:28,200 --> 01:50:32,120
I won’t let you take Ateş
from me right in front of my eyes.

1300
01:50:33,360 --> 01:50:35,080
There’s no other option.

1301
01:50:36,040 --> 01:50:37,600
You’re going to learn the truth…

1302
01:50:38,600 --> 01:50:40,680
… why he came here.

1303
01:50:41,080 --> 01:50:43,120
His revenge plan…

1304
01:50:43,200 --> 01:50:46,480
… everything… you'll find out everything.

1305
01:50:48,080 --> 01:50:50,320
And then we’ll see if you still love him…

1306
01:50:51,320 --> 01:50:53,640
… if you still stand beside him.

1307
01:51:12,960 --> 01:51:15,800
Why is he questioning so
much that I worry about him?

1308
01:51:17,960 --> 01:51:20,320
Why is he reading into it?

1309
01:51:22,480 --> 01:51:26,040
What’s wrong with caring about someone?

1310
01:51:32,440 --> 01:51:36,360
Unless… unless it’s more than that?

1311
01:51:48,720 --> 01:51:51,080
It’s like… my eyes keep searching for him.

1312
01:51:53,480 --> 01:51:57,960
My heart jumps every time I look at him.

1313
01:52:06,800 --> 01:52:08,800
What is happening to me?

1314
01:52:09,320 --> 01:52:11,520
What is this feeling
everyone sees except me?

1315
01:52:27,800 --> 01:52:29,880
Don’t be ridiculous, Mercan.

1316
01:52:30,840 --> 01:52:32,480
Don’t be ridiculous.

1317
01:52:33,320 --> 01:52:36,280
Don’t get carried away
with unnecessary thoughts.

1318
01:52:36,800 --> 01:52:38,280
There's no need for that.

1319
01:52:38,360 --> 01:52:41,280
There’s nothing. Stay calm.

1320
01:52:52,440 --> 01:52:55,880
My God, then why am I this uneasy?

1321
01:53:09,920 --> 01:53:11,560
Why are you beating like this?

1322
01:53:12,840 --> 01:53:16,000
Enough, already. Stop.

1323
01:53:22,560 --> 01:53:23,760
Just a joke.

1324
01:54:10,360 --> 01:54:11,560
What are you doing?

1325
01:54:13,040 --> 01:54:14,320
Why did you run away?

1326
01:54:17,920 --> 01:54:20,480
No, I didn't.

1327
01:54:30,080 --> 01:54:31,960
Just in time.

1328
01:54:49,000 --> 01:54:52,280
♪ The sweetest song ♪

1329
01:54:52,360 --> 01:54:57,080
♪ I’ve ever heard is your voice. ♪

1330
01:54:57,920 --> 01:55:03,400
♪ The most beautiful image ♪

1331
01:55:03,480 --> 01:55:06,720
♪ I’ve ever seen is your face. ♪

1332
01:55:06,960 --> 01:55:11,440
♪ You’re the softest flower
I’ve ever breathed in, ♪

1333
01:55:11,520 --> 01:55:15,360
♪ the most exquisite
taste I’ve ever known. ♪

1334
01:55:15,520 --> 01:55:20,400
♪ The only sacred place
these hands have touched ♪

1335
01:55:20,480 --> 01:55:23,640
♪ is the temple of your skin. ♪

1336
01:55:23,840 --> 01:55:28,160
♪ You are my senses, my gentleness, ♪

1337
01:55:28,240 --> 01:55:34,120
♪ the deepest feeling I’ve ever felt. ♪

1338
01:55:37,280 --> 01:55:41,240
♪ I love you more than I can say. ♪

1339
01:55:41,320 --> 01:55:46,880
♪ You’re God’s precious gift,
♪ ♪ and at last… I found you. ♪

1340
01:55:47,240 --> 01:55:50,320
♪ If only you knew how long I searched. ♪

1341
01:55:50,400 --> 01:55:56,080
♪ Forgive me, if I
made you wait too long. ♪

1342
01:55:56,360 --> 01:55:59,200
♪ I love you—truly, endlessly. ♪

1343
01:55:59,280 --> 01:56:05,000
♪ God’s beautiful gift… ♪
♪ and at last… I found you. ♪

1344
01:56:05,120 --> 01:56:08,200
♪ Thank you. ♪

1345
01:56:08,280 --> 01:56:11,160
♪ Thank you to the One above ♪

1346
01:56:11,280 --> 01:56:15,000
♪ for writing you into my fate. ♪

1347
01:56:32,360 --> 01:56:35,000
♪ The sweetest song ♪

1348
01:56:35,080 --> 01:56:36,240
My God… is this a dream?

1349
01:56:36,840 --> 01:56:42,360
♪ I’ve ever heard is your
voice. The most beautiful image ♪

1350
01:56:42,440 --> 01:56:44,360
I wish we could stay like this forever.

1351
01:56:44,440 --> 01:56:50,200
♪ I’ve ever seen is your face. ♪

1352
01:56:50,440 --> 01:56:54,640
♪ You’re the softest flower
♪ ♪ I’ve ever breathed in, ♪

1353
01:56:54,920 --> 01:56:59,040
♪ the most exquisite
taste I’ve ever known. ♪

1354
01:56:59,400 --> 01:57:02,320
♪ The only sacred place
these hands have touched ♪

1355
01:57:02,440 --> 01:57:06,400
♪ is the temple of your skin. ♪

1356
01:57:07,280 --> 01:57:10,800
♪ You are my senses, my gentleness, ♪

1357
01:57:11,720 --> 01:57:16,720
♪ the deepest feeling I’ve ever felt. ♪

1358
01:57:18,600 --> 01:57:20,800
It's time.

1359
01:57:25,040 --> 01:57:27,280
There are things we need to talk about.

1360
01:57:38,280 --> 01:57:39,960
I…

1361
01:57:45,720 --> 01:57:48,400
Where are you going, Mercan?

1362
01:57:49,440 --> 01:57:51,200
Ahh...

1363
01:57:56,880 --> 01:57:59,800
Mercan! Stop! What's wrong with you?!

1364
01:58:14,560 --> 01:58:15,880
Where are you Mercan?

1365
01:58:22,560 --> 01:58:24,040
Mercan!

1366
01:58:31,560 --> 01:58:33,400
What are you doing?

1367
01:58:33,520 --> 01:58:36,760
What's wrong with you?
Why are you running away?

1368
01:58:38,320 --> 01:58:40,080
Let go!

1369
01:58:47,280 --> 01:58:49,880
Hold still. Your hair is full of leaves.

1370
01:58:54,760 --> 01:58:57,520
It doesn’t matter. Just let me go.

1371
01:59:00,920 --> 01:59:02,360
Calm down.

1372
01:59:07,080 --> 01:59:08,440
What happened to you?

1373
01:59:09,080 --> 01:59:10,960
Nothing happened! What could have happened?

1374
01:59:11,640 --> 01:59:13,240
Then why were you running from me?

1375
01:59:13,440 --> 01:59:15,280
Then why didn’t you stop when I called you?

1376
01:59:16,880 --> 01:59:18,960
Because you were running!

1377
01:59:19,640 --> 01:59:22,400
-Because I ran? -Mm‑hmm.

1378
01:59:22,920 --> 01:59:24,920
I ran because you were running.

1379
01:59:26,080 --> 01:59:29,640
I mean… that’s not what happened!

1380
01:59:36,840 --> 01:59:38,440
Let me go!

1381
01:59:38,520 --> 01:59:40,120
I can’t. Not until I say this.

1382
01:59:44,320 --> 01:59:45,520
Say what?

1383
01:59:50,720 --> 01:59:52,560
I know you were terrified for me today.

1384
01:59:52,960 --> 01:59:54,480
You were devastated.

1385
01:59:54,920 --> 01:59:56,560
Why?

1386
01:59:58,600 --> 01:59:59,880
What “why”?

1387
02:00:00,160 --> 02:00:01,800
Because I thought you were dead!

1388
02:00:02,960 --> 02:00:05,080
I was sad. Isn’t that enough?

1389
02:00:05,160 --> 02:00:06,960
Isn’t that normal?

1390
02:00:09,240 --> 02:00:12,560
Is that all? Nothing more?

1391
02:00:14,680 --> 02:00:16,080
Yes! That’s all!

1392
02:00:19,080 --> 02:00:21,200
What else do you want me to say?

1393
02:00:22,120 --> 02:00:23,560
Just let me go!

1394
02:00:24,640 --> 02:00:26,440
It won’t matter if you run.

1395
02:00:27,880 --> 02:00:29,400
Because you…

1396
02:00:39,440 --> 02:00:41,400
…You're right here in my heart.

1397
02:00:46,720 --> 02:00:48,680
And you’re the one who can heal it.

1398
02:00:52,560 --> 02:00:54,320
You’re the light in all my darkness.

1399
02:00:58,040 --> 02:01:02,160
What are you talking about?
What "darkness"? What "light"?

1400
02:01:04,520 --> 02:01:06,560
Do you understand?

1401
02:01:09,520 --> 02:01:11,400
No!

1402
02:01:16,000 --> 02:01:17,520
When you look at me like that,

1403
02:01:18,320 --> 02:01:20,160
my heart can’t stay in my chest.

1404
02:01:25,080 --> 02:01:28,160
I forget how to breathe.

1405
02:01:28,840 --> 02:01:33,400
One smile from you and every
storm inside me goes quiet.

1406
02:01:34,600 --> 02:01:38,920
I feel like I can overcome anything.

1407
02:01:43,520 --> 02:01:47,440
You’re the heart of my
heart… my pearl, Mercan.

1408
02:01:58,200 --> 02:02:00,920
Whose pearl?

1409
02:02:02,280 --> 02:02:05,320
I'm telling you! Your scent is in my chest.

1410
02:02:05,640 --> 02:02:07,560
I’m gone for you. Get it?

1411
02:02:19,320 --> 02:02:22,200
Do you understand? Can you hear me, Mercan?

1412
02:02:26,320 --> 02:02:28,600
Look at me. Look into my eyes, Mercan.

1413
02:02:35,640 --> 02:02:40,200
Every part of me is in
love with every part of you.

1414
02:02:54,320 --> 02:02:55,720
What are you saying?

1415
02:02:56,360 --> 02:02:59,160
Again with these "Look at me" commands?

1416
02:03:01,520 --> 02:03:03,960
I’m saying you’ve taken over my heart!

1417
02:03:13,040 --> 02:03:15,040
I love you! I love you.

1418
02:03:16,920 --> 02:03:18,760
I love you! I love you.

1419
02:03:20,200 --> 02:03:21,920
Do you understand?

1420
02:03:29,240 --> 02:03:32,760
Did he say he loved me?

1421
02:05:49,800 --> 02:05:52,400
Look at me. Don't cry.

1422
02:05:53,480 --> 02:05:54,560
I don't like whiny people.

1423
02:05:56,400 --> 02:05:57,760
Please, go away.

1424
02:05:58,120 --> 02:05:59,240
Stay away from me.

1425
02:06:02,800 --> 02:06:04,119
Why are you still here? Go away!

1426
02:06:04,120 --> 02:06:06,960
I told you to go away! Go! Leave!

1427
02:08:15,280 --> 02:08:19,160
"I'd rather pay the price
of love than live without it."

1428
02:08:52,760 --> 02:08:53,760
Leave it, I can handle.

1429
02:08:54,040 --> 02:08:54,540
No.

1430
02:08:54,920 --> 02:08:55,960
You'll cut your hand.

1431
02:08:56,360 --> 02:08:56,860
I won't.

1432
02:08:57,000 --> 02:08:58,800
You'll cut if you do like this.

1433
02:09:04,400 --> 02:09:05,400
Look what you did.

1434
02:09:05,720 --> 02:09:06,720
Did it cut?

1435
02:09:11,480 --> 02:09:12,480
Come.
We should clean.

1436
02:10:03,720 --> 02:10:05,040
It's nothing.
You're exaggerating.

1437
02:10:05,800 --> 02:10:06,800
I'm not.

1438
02:10:07,240 --> 02:10:08,280
You're not listening.

1439
02:10:40,200 --> 02:10:41,200
I said so.

1440
02:10:44,240 --> 02:10:46,360
Okay, I misunderstood.

1441
02:10:47,720 --> 02:10:48,720
I shall go.

1442
02:10:48,760 --> 02:10:49,760
I'll come after one hour.

1443
02:10:55,160 --> 02:10:56,160
If you let me.

1444
02:10:58,920 --> 02:10:59,920
Why are you here?

1445
02:11:04,120 --> 02:11:05,240
The meeting wasn't here.

1446
02:11:08,200 --> 02:11:09,680
I don't know, I thought it was here.

1447
02:11:10,400 --> 02:11:12,200
Isn't this a workroom?

1448
02:11:19,960 --> 02:11:21,160
So you misunderstood that too.

1449
02:11:22,520 --> 02:11:23,560
Just like the hour.

1450
02:11:25,280 --> 02:11:26,560
Yes I misunderstood.

1451
02:11:30,920 --> 02:11:32,280
Why all these questions?

1452
02:11:33,200 --> 02:11:33,700
As if

1453
02:11:34,160 --> 02:11:35,520
I had done something wrong.

1454
02:11:35,960 --> 02:11:37,200
You've really dragged this out.

1455
02:11:37,240 --> 02:11:38,840
Okay, I misunderstood. I'll go.

1456
02:11:39,000 --> 02:11:40,000
I'll come after one hour.

1457
02:12:04,320 --> 02:12:06,080
You can't tell a lie, you know that, right?

1458
02:12:12,120 --> 02:12:13,120
Okay.

1459
02:12:13,920 --> 02:12:14,920
Yes, I know.

1460
02:12:15,920 --> 02:12:17,080
Everyone says so.

1461
02:12:18,480 --> 02:12:19,760
I don't like to tell lie.

1462
02:12:20,840 --> 02:12:22,160
Sometimes you just have to do it.

1463
02:12:24,520 --> 02:12:25,800
I can't do that either.

1464
02:12:28,600 --> 02:12:29,600
Why are you here then?

1465
02:12:32,040 --> 02:12:33,080
Well, I have a guess.

1466
02:13:06,320 --> 02:13:07,320
I'm sorry.

1467
02:13:07,400 --> 02:13:10,040
I didn't realize you were inside.
Otherwise, I wouldn't have come.

1468
02:13:12,080 --> 02:13:13,080
It's okay.

1469
02:13:33,400 --> 02:13:34,400
Were you impressed?

1470
02:13:36,520 --> 02:13:37,520
God.

1471
02:13:40,400 --> 02:13:41,520
Why am I impressed?

1472
02:14:27,440 --> 02:14:29,120
Did you find the answer that you look for?

1473
02:14:31,960 --> 02:14:32,960
Not yet.

1474
02:14:36,440 --> 02:14:37,440
But I'll.

1475
02:14:39,880 --> 02:14:41,240
Don't you think that I'll give up.

1476
02:14:42,720 --> 02:14:44,960
When I set out on a
path, I walk it to the end.

1477
02:14:45,360 --> 02:14:46,360
I don't go back.

1478
02:15:10,160 --> 02:15:11,160
Of course, go.

1479
02:15:11,840 --> 02:15:12,840
All the ways are yours.

1480
02:16:57,960 --> 02:16:59,480
How innocent she looks.

1481
02:17:28,760 --> 02:17:30,160
Could you have done it?

1482
02:18:03,000 --> 02:18:04,200
You're confusing me.

1483
02:19:44,080 --> 02:19:47,080
How sleep makes even the most
ruthless person seem innocent.

1484
02:19:48,960 --> 02:19:50,520
As if all those harsh words

1485
02:19:51,200 --> 02:19:52,560
hateful glances

1486
02:19:53,560 --> 02:19:55,480
as if they belonged to
someone else, not to him.

1487
02:21:07,040 --> 02:21:08,080
Why did she cover me up?

1488
02:21:11,320 --> 02:21:12,800
She surprises me every time.
